1
00:00:10,310 --> 00:00:14,114
[It's The Morning Of The Final Day]

2
00:00:18,352 --> 00:00:20,487
Seung Won, my hair keeps falling flat.

3
00:00:20,487 --> 00:00:21,688
Can I wear a bandana?

4
00:00:21,688 --> 00:00:23,824
- No.
- I can't wear one?

5
00:00:23,824 --> 00:00:25,692
- What about a hat?
- Wear an umbrella.

6
00:00:25,692 --> 00:00:26,927
Wear an umbrella while filming.

7
00:00:26,927 --> 00:00:29,096
[He Just Slays Seon Ho]
What if I wear a hat backwards?

8
00:00:29,096 --> 00:00:30,430
No, you need to wear it properly.

9
00:00:30,430 --> 00:00:31,590
It needs to be right side up.

10
00:00:31,999 --> 00:00:33,300
But those pants...

11
00:00:33,300 --> 00:00:35,302
I think flared pants would be better.

12
00:00:35,302 --> 00:00:37,271
- What he wore earlier, right?
- Yeah.

13
00:00:37,271 --> 00:00:38,472
- It was better.
- This one's too...

14
00:00:38,472 --> 00:00:40,407
- It's too...
- I look too much like a laborer, right?

15
00:00:40,407 --> 00:00:42,009
It's like a factory uniform.

16
00:00:42,009 --> 00:00:43,744
[Ki Taek's Styling Is Up To Them]
Okay, when I'm working...

17
00:00:43,744 --> 00:00:45,879
You really look like a factory worker.

18
00:00:47,314 --> 00:00:49,483
[Seung Won's Suggested Outfit]
I wasn't going to wear this.

19
00:00:49,483 --> 00:00:51,018
[A Clean Look With Flared Pants]
since I've worn it before.

20
00:00:51,018 --> 00:00:53,320
I like the jacket and pants.

21
00:00:53,320 --> 00:00:54,888
Open your jacket.

22
00:00:54,888 --> 00:00:55,888
Do this.

23
00:00:57,357 --> 00:00:59,860
[A Completely Different Vibe]

24
00:00:59,860 --> 00:01:02,829
The T-shirt you wore yesterday was better.

25
00:01:02,829 --> 00:01:05,032
- The white shirt, right?
- Yes, the white one.

26
00:01:05,999 --> 00:01:08,635
[Changing Into The White T-Shirt]

27
00:01:08,635 --> 00:01:10,437
This looks way better.

28
00:01:10,437 --> 00:01:13,640
[Feeling Pleased With Himself]
The navy doesn't work.

29
00:01:13,640 --> 00:01:14,808
Thanks, Seung Won.

30
00:01:14,808 --> 00:01:16,810
You're always thanking me.

31
00:01:16,810 --> 00:01:19,279
[Joking]
Show me with a gift.

32
00:01:19,279 --> 00:01:20,380
Okay.

33
00:01:20,380 --> 00:01:22,316
What are you going to give me?

34
00:01:22,316 --> 00:01:24,952
I'll think about what to get you.

35
00:01:24,952 --> 00:01:26,119
That's the outfit for today.

36
00:01:26,119 --> 00:01:29,000
- Yes, I'll go with this.
- That's the look.

37
00:01:31,391 --> 00:01:34,020
I've gotten really close to Ki Taek.

38
00:01:34,020 --> 00:01:36,196
That's what happens

39
00:01:36,196 --> 00:01:38,532
- if you share a room for a few days.
- Yes.

40
00:01:38,532 --> 00:01:42,436
- You get unbelievably close.
- You do.

41
00:01:42,436 --> 00:01:44,037
- That's so true.
- Yeah.

42
00:01:44,037 --> 00:01:47,507
It's more than just working together.

43
00:01:47,507 --> 00:01:51,178
- We shared a room and shared meals...
- Yeah, we ate together

44
00:01:51,178 --> 00:01:56,316
and talked a lot,
so we've gotten really close.

45
00:01:57,050 --> 00:01:58,785
[The Three Men,
Who Have Formed A Tight Bond,]

46
00:01:58,785 --> 00:02:01,355
[Make Their Final Trip To Work Together]

47
00:02:13,634 --> 00:02:15,168
- It's so well-built.
- It's so impressive.

48
00:02:15,168 --> 00:02:17,671
- Isn't it so pretty?
- It's so pretty.

49
00:02:17,671 --> 00:02:18,839
I think that every time I see it.

50
00:02:18,839 --> 00:02:21,875
[We Can't Stop Admiring
How Pretty Our Bakery Is]

51
00:02:27,147 --> 00:02:28,779
Today's the final day.

52
00:02:29,349 --> 00:02:31,059
It's the last day.

53
00:02:33,153 --> 00:02:36,657
[Today Is Day 6 Of Bonjour Bakery]

54
00:02:37,858 --> 00:02:41,762
[It Is Our Final Day]

55
00:02:57,077 --> 00:02:59,079
This is my last coffee here.

56
00:03:00,380 --> 00:03:01,915
I feel so weird.

57
00:03:01,915 --> 00:03:03,917
I didn't want to act like this...

58
00:03:07,621 --> 00:03:09,556
- Hello.
- Hello.

59
00:03:09,556 --> 00:03:11,324
- Have a nice day.
- All right.

60
00:03:11,324 --> 00:03:13,026
- Today's our last day.
- Is it?

61
00:03:13,026 --> 00:03:14,161
Yes.

62
00:03:14,161 --> 00:03:15,862
- If you have time-
- What a shame.

63
00:03:15,862 --> 00:03:18,331
- It is a shame.
- Yes, it is.

64
00:03:18,331 --> 00:03:20,534
I'm in a weird mood.

65
00:03:20,534 --> 00:03:21,968
- Are you sad?
- Yes.

66
00:03:21,968 --> 00:03:23,036
I liked it here.

67
00:03:23,036 --> 00:03:25,205
- You liked being here?
- Yes.

68
00:03:25,205 --> 00:03:26,934
- Thank you.
- Bye.

69
00:03:27,507 --> 00:03:30,444
- It's a shame. I just got attached.
- Me too.

70
00:03:30,444 --> 00:03:31,945
- I'm in a strange mood.
- Isn't it a little sad?

71
00:03:31,945 --> 00:03:33,046
Yes, I feel sad.

72
00:03:33,046 --> 00:03:34,281
Oh, man.

73
00:03:34,281 --> 00:03:35,559
Oh, dear.

74
00:03:53,400 --> 00:03:55,335
<i>My grandmother...</i>

75
00:03:56,970 --> 00:03:59,506
recently passed away.

76
00:03:59,506 --> 00:04:01,975
- She lived alone in a nursing home.
- I see.

77
00:04:01,975 --> 00:04:04,511
My family and I often visited but...

78
00:04:04,511 --> 00:04:05,912
Seeing them reminds me of her.

79
00:04:05,912 --> 00:04:08,916
[Seon Ho Was Grieving For His Grandmother]

80
00:04:08,916 --> 00:04:11,516
I'm upset that not many people came by.

81
00:04:14,354 --> 00:04:15,655
You don't have to put it in there.

82
00:04:15,655 --> 00:04:18,258
- I'll just take...
- I have to because that's the rule.

83
00:04:18,258 --> 00:04:20,360
I'm just a part-timer.
The manager will scold me if I don't.

84
00:04:20,360 --> 00:04:22,020
You're a part-time employee?

85
00:04:22,996 --> 00:04:23,997
You're such a talker.

86
00:04:23,997 --> 00:04:25,732
I'll get a loaf of bread tomorrow.

87
00:04:25,732 --> 00:04:27,901
You already bought this,
and you're going to spend more?

88
00:04:27,901 --> 00:04:29,509
Tomorrow...

89
00:04:30,403 --> 00:04:34,007
[This Place Was Extra Special To Seon Ho]

90
00:04:44,184 --> 00:04:49,756
[It's A Shame The Last Day Has Come So Soon]

91
00:04:58,698 --> 00:05:03,103
[The Manager Is On Her Way To Work]

92
00:05:04,771 --> 00:05:05,839
Hello, Hee Ae.

93
00:05:05,839 --> 00:05:07,374
Hello.

94
00:05:07,374 --> 00:05:09,109
It's our last day.

95
00:05:09,109 --> 00:05:10,710
It's the final day.

96
00:05:10,710 --> 00:05:12,712
Good morning.

97
00:05:12,712 --> 00:05:16,483
- I've been in a weird mood since earlier.
- You too?

98
00:05:16,483 --> 00:05:18,118
So...

99
00:05:18,118 --> 00:05:20,854
Everything feels more meaningful today,

100
00:05:20,854 --> 00:05:22,589
even drinking coffee.

101
00:05:22,589 --> 00:05:24,724
- Really?
- Even while cleaning, I felt a bit...

102
00:05:24,724 --> 00:05:27,460
I'm grateful you feel the same way.

103
00:05:27,460 --> 00:05:28,896
Do you also feel a bit sad?

104
00:05:28,896 --> 00:05:33,166
I get really sad when filming wraps up.

105
00:05:33,166 --> 00:05:34,868
When other actors move on to new projects

106
00:05:34,868 --> 00:05:36,336
all happy and excited,

107
00:05:36,336 --> 00:05:38,538
- it's a bit upsetting.
- You feel weird, right?

108
00:05:38,538 --> 00:05:40,707
- Do you know that feeling?
- I'm the same way.

109
00:05:40,707 --> 00:05:41,875
- But for me,
- Really?

110
00:05:41,875 --> 00:05:44,010
I don't cry when filming wraps up,

111
00:05:44,010 --> 00:05:47,047
but the sadness lingers for a while.

112
00:05:47,047 --> 00:05:48,949
- When it ends...
- Isn't it a special feeling?

113
00:05:48,949 --> 00:05:51,418
Yes, and today...

114
00:05:51,418 --> 00:05:53,553
- I'm feeling it constantly.
- Yes.

115
00:05:53,553 --> 00:05:55,422
I ran into an elderly woman, and she said,

116
00:05:55,422 --> 00:05:58,325
"It's a shame. I just got attached."

117
00:05:58,325 --> 00:05:59,960
That made me feel even more...

118
00:05:59,960 --> 00:06:03,096
That's the thing about this program.

119
00:06:03,096 --> 00:06:06,933
Small things like that mean so much.

120
00:06:06,933 --> 00:06:09,803
You know, there's really not much to life.

121
00:06:09,803 --> 00:06:13,406
It passes by in a flash.
I'll be in their position soon.

122
00:06:13,406 --> 00:06:16,710
Just eating three meals a day, nowhere to go

123
00:06:16,710 --> 00:06:19,312
taking medication,
and going in and out of hospitals.

124
00:06:19,312 --> 00:06:21,615
So, this place is...
Even I enjoy coming here.

125
00:06:21,615 --> 00:06:23,383
I prefer coming here over my other work.

126
00:06:23,383 --> 00:06:25,252
You make me a cup of coffee,

127
00:06:25,252 --> 00:06:27,153
and Ki Taek even makes us eggs...

128
00:06:27,153 --> 00:06:30,123
It's honestly all so meaningful.

129
00:06:30,123 --> 00:06:33,026
Having someone who cares means a lot.

130
00:06:33,026 --> 00:06:38,265
Just coming here and enjoying
coffee in this bright, open space...

131
00:06:38,265 --> 00:06:42,269
- I think it might be a first for them.
- I think so too.

132
00:06:42,269 --> 00:06:44,337
That makes it very meaningful.

133
00:06:44,337 --> 00:06:46,239
- It will stick with them for life.
- Totally.

134
00:06:46,239 --> 00:06:48,947
- It's a lasting memory.
- It's such a precious experience.

135
00:06:51,578 --> 00:06:55,215
[30 Minutes Before Opening]

136
00:06:56,298 --> 00:06:59,152
[A Customer Has Arrived Already]

137
00:06:59,152 --> 00:07:00,921
We have a customer!

138
00:07:03,023 --> 00:07:04,424
- Hello, ma'am.
- Hello!

139
00:07:04,424 --> 00:07:06,092
Can I buy something now?

140
00:07:06,092 --> 00:07:07,160
Can I buy something?

141
00:07:07,160 --> 00:07:09,029
- What do you need?
- Should I come back later?

142
00:07:09,029 --> 00:07:10,063
What would you like to buy?

143
00:07:10,063 --> 00:07:11,831
[Kim Sun Ja Bonjour Bakery VVVIP]

144
00:07:11,831 --> 00:07:12,899
Is that all you're selling?

145
00:07:12,899 --> 00:07:14,234
That's all we have right now.

146
00:07:14,234 --> 00:07:18,171
The loaf will be ready in the afternoon,
around 1 p.m.

147
00:07:18,171 --> 00:07:19,906
- I'll come back.
- Will you come back?

148
00:07:19,906 --> 00:07:22,542
- I'll put one aside for you.
- Okay.

149
00:07:22,542 --> 00:07:23,907
[1 Cha Loaf Bread For Kim Sun Ja]
There's a limited amount.

150
00:07:26,212 --> 00:07:29,015
- Isn't it nice to be out like this?
- Yes.

151
00:07:29,015 --> 00:07:32,145
Even if it's tiring,
it's not good to stay home all the time.

152
00:07:33,286 --> 00:07:35,309
- See you later, ma'am!
- Yes.

153
00:07:39,225 --> 00:07:43,330
[Someone Else Makes Their Way To The Bakery]

154
00:07:46,933 --> 00:07:51,204
[While The Hall Team Makes
The Final Preparations]

155
00:08:02,516 --> 00:08:04,480
[What?]

156
00:08:05,151 --> 00:08:06,586
That startled me.

157
00:08:06,586 --> 00:08:07,887
Look who it is!

158
00:08:07,887 --> 00:08:11,024
[A Welcome Face, Even From A Distance]

159
00:08:11,024 --> 00:08:12,892
- Hello!
- Look who it is!

160
00:08:12,892 --> 00:08:14,227
[Part-Timer Chan Is Back!]
Hello.

161
00:08:14,227 --> 00:08:16,196
It's Dino. I never thought he'd come back.

162
00:08:16,196 --> 00:08:17,998
I heard about how you did.

163
00:08:17,998 --> 00:08:19,165
Oh, did you?

164
00:08:19,165 --> 00:08:20,400
I heard you worked really hard.

165
00:08:20,400 --> 00:08:22,469
- I heard you went through a lot.
- He worked so hard.

166
00:08:22,469 --> 00:08:24,429
- At this early hour...
- It's so nice to see you.

167
00:08:25,071 --> 00:08:26,973
- We meet again.
- Yes.

168
00:08:26,973 --> 00:08:28,074
Is someone here?

169
00:08:28,074 --> 00:08:29,309
- It's Dino.
- Oh, my gosh.

170
00:08:29,309 --> 00:08:30,310
- What on earth?
- Hello!

171
00:08:30,310 --> 00:08:32,679
I heard it's your last day of filming.

172
00:08:32,679 --> 00:08:36,082
- Really?
- We missed you.

173
00:08:36,082 --> 00:08:37,717
What a surprise.

174
00:08:37,717 --> 00:08:40,086
- Hello.
- You came all this way.

175
00:08:40,086 --> 00:08:42,002
- It's all good.
- My goodness.

176
00:08:43,556 --> 00:08:46,092
- I'm so moved.
- Seriously.

177
00:08:46,092 --> 00:08:48,495
- He asked us to invite him back
- Yes.

178
00:08:48,495 --> 00:08:50,130
- When we said goodbye.
- That's right.

179
00:08:50,130 --> 00:08:51,498
[He Rearranged His Schedule To Come Back ]
He said he wanted to come back.

180
00:08:51,498 --> 00:08:54,000
I thought you were only being courteous.

181
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:54,968
- What's that?
- What is it?

182
00:08:54,968 --> 00:08:59,105
I heard today was
your last day of filming,

183
00:08:59,105 --> 00:09:01,174
- so I got vitamins as a small gift.
- Leave them and go.

184
00:09:01,174 --> 00:09:02,442
[Vitamins He Prepared Himself]
Okay.

185
00:09:02,442 --> 00:09:03,876
- All right.
- This is unbelievable.

186
00:09:03,876 --> 00:09:05,011
You did well.

187
00:09:05,011 --> 00:09:06,279
This is great.

188
00:09:06,279 --> 00:09:07,814
- This is so nice.
- Thank you.

189
00:09:07,814 --> 00:09:11,684
- I wanted to help in a small way.
- This isn't small!

190
00:09:11,684 --> 00:09:13,920
I'll do whatever you need me to do today.

191
00:09:13,920 --> 00:09:15,655
- You plan to work while you're here?
- Yes.

192
00:09:15,655 --> 00:09:16,823
- Really?
- Are you serious?

193
00:09:16,823 --> 00:09:18,024
- I'm joining you.
- Really?

194
00:09:18,024 --> 00:09:19,892
- Oh, my gosh.
- This really is a surprise.

195
00:09:19,892 --> 00:09:22,595
[He Started With Us And Will Finish With Us]
We do need three people in the hall.

196
00:09:22,595 --> 00:09:23,730
Today will be...

197
00:09:23,730 --> 00:09:25,765
Do you want a shot of coffee first?

198
00:09:25,765 --> 00:09:27,166
- I'd love one.
- Iced Americano?

199
00:09:27,166 --> 00:09:28,067
Yes, thank you!

200
00:09:28,067 --> 00:09:29,669
- The Prince of the Hall.
- The prince.

201
00:09:29,669 --> 00:09:32,071
[The Prince Of The Hall Will Make The Coffee]

202
00:09:32,071 --> 00:09:33,506
Honestly, on the first day-

203
00:09:33,506 --> 00:09:34,941
I heard you made coffee nonstop.

204
00:09:34,941 --> 00:09:37,043
[Sharing Memories Of His First Day]
I didn't even really know how to make one,

205
00:09:37,043 --> 00:09:38,644
but somehow I managed.

206
00:09:38,644 --> 00:09:42,982
What a great kid.

207
00:09:43,950 --> 00:09:47,887
[Coffee Is Ready For Our Special Part-Timer]

208
00:09:48,654 --> 00:09:52,725
[Someone Else Is Deeply Touched By Chan]

209
00:09:52,725 --> 00:09:54,727
Did you come back
because you were worried about me?

210
00:09:54,727 --> 00:09:56,311
No, that's not it.

211
00:09:56,311 --> 00:10:00,266
I was only here for one day,
but I got so attached.

212
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:02,602
- Thank you.
- Not at all.

213
00:10:02,602 --> 00:10:05,638
[Bonjour Bakery]

214
00:10:11,878 --> 00:10:13,112
[Bonjour Green Barley Field Tart]

215
00:10:13,112 --> 00:10:19,052
[Introducing The Last New Items]

216
00:10:19,485 --> 00:10:21,687
[Today's New Morning Menu]

217
00:10:21,687 --> 00:10:24,757
[Bonjour Kumquat Forsythia Tart]

218
00:10:24,757 --> 00:10:30,296
[Bonjour Peanut Pain Au Chocolat]

219
00:10:30,296 --> 00:10:37,270
[Bonjour Cha Loaf Bread]

220
00:10:37,270 --> 00:10:39,105
Gosh, this is...

221
00:10:39,105 --> 00:10:40,840
This is hard.

222
00:10:40,840 --> 00:10:45,111
I'd rather make a hundred Saint-Honorés.

223
00:10:45,111 --> 00:10:48,086
This is the hardest thing I've made today.

224
00:10:48,614 --> 00:10:51,417
This one's the hardest for me.

225
00:10:51,417 --> 00:10:53,986
- The forsythia...
<i>- Forsythia.</i>

226
00:10:53,986 --> 00:10:55,955
[Today's Ingredient
Is A Forsythia Shade Of Yellow]

227
00:10:55,955 --> 00:10:58,327
I want to do my best.

228
00:10:59,058 --> 00:11:01,327
I want to make it look nice.

229
00:11:02,462 --> 00:11:05,131
Desire. Desperation.

230
00:11:06,165 --> 00:11:09,035
[Even The King Of Baking
Is Nervous About Today's Dessert]

231
00:11:10,169 --> 00:11:13,573
[Bonjour Kumquat Forsythia Tart]

232
00:11:14,073 --> 00:11:16,309
- Let's start with kumquats.
- All right.

233
00:11:16,309 --> 00:11:18,669
[The King Of Baking's Guide
Start With Prepping The Kumquats]

234
00:11:22,415 --> 00:11:26,552
[Remove The Stems And Slice Them In Half]

235
00:11:26,986 --> 00:11:29,160
[Press Gently To Squeeze Out The Seeds]

236
00:11:29,160 --> 00:11:30,156
It smells so nice.

237
00:11:30,156 --> 00:11:32,792
[The Refreshing Citrus Scent Fills The Room]

238
00:11:34,519 --> 00:11:35,695
[Candied Kumquats]

239
00:11:35,695 --> 00:11:38,197
[Simmer The Seeded Kumquats
In A Sweet Syrup]

240
00:11:39,866 --> 00:11:41,801
[Check Its Softness]

241
00:11:43,669 --> 00:11:45,905
- This is good enough, right?
- Yes.

242
00:11:45,905 --> 00:11:47,907
[Once The Peel Is Translucent,
Take It Off The Heat]

243
00:11:49,142 --> 00:11:53,312
[Drain The Candied Kumquats In A Sieve
And Let Them Cool Slightly]

244
00:11:53,880 --> 00:11:55,615
Help me with this.

245
00:11:55,615 --> 00:11:56,795
Hold it up.

246
00:11:58,584 --> 00:12:01,921
[A Determined Look To Do His Best]
<i>I want to do my best.</i>

247
00:12:01,921 --> 00:12:04,790
[A Gentle Touch To Make It Look Nicer]
<i>I want to make it look nice.</i>

248
00:12:05,925 --> 00:12:07,746
It's so hot!

249
00:12:08,961 --> 00:12:11,597
- When it plumps up,
- Yes?

250
00:12:11,597 --> 00:12:13,866
- place it here, Ki Taek.
- Okay.

251
00:12:13,866 --> 00:12:16,669
And then, pinch the sides slightly.

252
00:12:16,669 --> 00:12:19,272
[Gently Pinch Both Ends
To Get The Desired Shape]

253
00:12:19,906 --> 00:12:21,407
- Let's do it together.
- Okay.

254
00:12:21,407 --> 00:12:23,342
It's all right since they've cooled.

255
00:12:24,577 --> 00:12:25,612
It's really hot.

256
00:12:25,612 --> 00:12:26,947
[Throws It Down]

257
00:12:27,480 --> 00:12:30,283
[His Fingers Are Too Sensitive
To Be The King Of Baking]

258
00:12:31,250 --> 00:12:33,819
[I'll Endure The Heat]
Pinch the bottom...

259
00:12:33,819 --> 00:12:35,588
Pinch them...

260
00:12:35,588 --> 00:12:37,395
Flatten it like this...

261
00:12:38,958 --> 00:12:40,293
- Just like this.
- That's it.

262
00:12:40,293 --> 00:12:43,229
Once you've placed it down,
pinch the sides again,

263
00:12:43,229 --> 00:12:45,131
- like this.
- I see.

264
00:12:45,131 --> 00:12:46,306
All right, then.

265
00:12:46,866 --> 00:12:48,334
- Should we get started? - Yes.

266
00:12:48,334 --> 00:12:50,203
[Ready To Finish The Kumquat Forsythia Tart]

267
00:12:51,938 --> 00:12:55,141
[Kumquat Coulis]

268
00:12:55,141 --> 00:12:58,044
[Ki Taek Neatly Arranges The Kumquats]

269
00:13:03,149 --> 00:13:06,252
[4 Candied Kumquats Are Placed On Top]

270
00:13:15,528 --> 00:13:20,132
[The Rest Of The Tart
Is Filled With Kumquat Cream]

271
00:13:28,608 --> 00:13:33,179
[Evenly Spread The Cream]

272
00:13:34,113 --> 00:13:35,514
- That's done.
- Okay.

273
00:13:38,584 --> 00:13:42,521
[Billowy Petals Of Yogurt Monté Cream]

274
00:13:47,593 --> 00:13:49,962
[Did You See That?]

275
00:13:51,964 --> 00:13:54,267
[He Is Truly The King Of Baking]

276
00:13:56,135 --> 00:13:59,105
[I Am The King Of Baking,
And I Am Drunk On Success]

277
00:14:04,877 --> 00:14:07,480
[The Highlight Of The Kumquat Forsythia Tart]

278
00:14:07,980 --> 00:14:10,750
[A Single Candied Kumquat
Atop The Pillowy Cream]

279
00:14:18,090 --> 00:14:20,693
[Slice Of Fragrant Kumquat Peel
For Added Flavor]

280
00:14:22,461 --> 00:14:24,563
[Finishing Touches With Gold]

281
00:14:36,042 --> 00:14:38,477
The King of Baking!

282
00:14:38,477 --> 00:14:40,413
The Prince of the Hall!

283
00:14:41,080 --> 00:14:43,642
A baking revolutionary!

284
00:14:47,320 --> 00:14:48,721
Ta-da.

285
00:14:51,257 --> 00:14:52,825
"Bonjour..."

286
00:14:52,825 --> 00:14:54,627
[We Are Open]

287
00:14:57,663 --> 00:15:01,767
[Ringing The Bell For The Last Time]

288
00:15:01,767 --> 00:15:03,903
[Seon Ho Delegates The Tasks]
Dino, just make the orangeades today.

289
00:15:03,903 --> 00:15:06,305
I'll handle the coffees.

290
00:15:06,305 --> 00:15:09,709
- Just the orangeades?
- Yes, just handle the orangeades.

291
00:15:09,709 --> 00:15:11,243
We can't touch the honey.

292
00:15:11,243 --> 00:15:14,213
- It's handled by a top pro.
- Okay.

293
00:15:14,213 --> 00:15:16,015
- Don't touch the honey.
- Aren't you the pro?

294
00:15:16,015 --> 00:15:18,484
[The Queen Of Lemon Tea]
No, it's Hee Ae.

295
00:15:18,484 --> 00:15:22,355
- She can now make three cups at once.
- Wow, really?

296
00:15:22,355 --> 00:15:26,325
[Making 3 Cups Of Lemon Honey Tea
Is A Piece Of Cake Now]

297
00:15:26,859 --> 00:15:28,127
Should we go in?

298
00:15:28,127 --> 00:15:29,777
Yes, let's go in.

299
00:15:31,030 --> 00:15:33,299
- Hello.
- Hello, come on in.

300
00:15:33,299 --> 00:15:34,224
Have you been well?

301
00:15:34,224 --> 00:15:35,768
- Yes.
- Of course.

302
00:15:35,768 --> 00:15:37,103
Aren't you a regular?

303
00:15:37,103 --> 00:15:38,771
Sit over here.

304
00:15:38,771 --> 00:15:41,874
I came here to see you all today.

305
00:15:41,874 --> 00:15:43,409
I know. Thank you

306
00:15:43,409 --> 00:15:46,145
- for coming so often.
- We came because you're so pretty.

307
00:15:46,946 --> 00:15:48,948
[Chan Brings The Warm Towels And Menu]

308
00:15:48,948 --> 00:15:50,349
Good job.

309
00:15:51,751 --> 00:15:54,271
Take your time with the menu,
and let me know when you're ready.

310
00:15:54,958 --> 00:15:56,021
Do you see?

311
00:15:56,021 --> 00:15:59,290
Just one extra person,
and everything runs smoothly.

312
00:15:59,290 --> 00:16:01,360
[Kim Yeong Suk, Na Tae Hwan,
Shin Yeong Sun, Im Chae Dong]

313
00:16:01,360 --> 00:16:04,530
- This is <i>bokbunja</i> flavor.
- Yeah.

314
00:16:04,530 --> 00:16:08,167
Bring us enough of these for five people.

315
00:16:08,167 --> 00:16:09,668
- This one and...
- That one.

316
00:16:09,668 --> 00:16:12,171
- Enough for five people?
- Yes.

317
00:16:12,171 --> 00:16:13,506
Welcome.

318
00:16:14,440 --> 00:16:15,775
Welcome.

319
00:16:16,642 --> 00:16:20,279
[First-Time Husband-And-Wife Customers]

320
00:16:20,780 --> 00:16:22,481
- Hello.
- It's nice to meet you.

321
00:16:22,481 --> 00:16:23,749
- Nice to meet you.
- Hello.

322
00:16:23,749 --> 00:16:25,584
Due to our regulations,

323
00:16:25,584 --> 00:16:28,954
- one of you must be over 65 years old.
- Yes.

324
00:16:28,954 --> 00:16:30,322
- We're both over 65.
- We're both over 65.

325
00:16:30,322 --> 00:16:31,524
I see.

326
00:16:31,524 --> 00:16:34,067
- May I see your ID? You look young.
- Okay.

327
00:16:35,461 --> 00:16:37,730
- You'll be shocked.
- Why?

328
00:16:37,730 --> 00:16:39,298
My eyes aren't very good.

329
00:16:39,298 --> 00:16:41,066
[Glasses At The Ready]

330
00:16:41,066 --> 00:16:42,318
What?

331
00:16:42,935 --> 00:16:44,103
But...

332
00:16:44,103 --> 00:16:46,071
This can't be real.

333
00:16:46,071 --> 00:16:48,073
It is real.

334
00:16:48,073 --> 00:16:50,242
- Were you born in the Year of the Dragon?
- Yes.

335
00:16:50,242 --> 00:16:53,179
My mother was born in the same year, 1940.

336
00:16:53,179 --> 00:16:55,247
- I'm the same age as your mother?
- Yes.

337
00:16:55,247 --> 00:16:57,783
[She's The Same Age As Hee Ae's Mother]
But how can you look so...

338
00:16:58,217 --> 00:16:59,952
Are you both the same age?

339
00:16:59,952 --> 00:17:01,153
No.

340
00:17:01,153 --> 00:17:02,888
- I'm older.
- She's older.

341
00:17:02,888 --> 00:17:04,623
- And you're married?
- Yes.

342
00:17:04,623 --> 00:17:06,158
[A Couple With A Twelve-Year Age Gap]
I've got goosebumps.

343
00:17:06,158 --> 00:17:07,927
Take a look at the menu

344
00:17:07,927 --> 00:17:11,330
while I get over my shock.

345
00:17:11,330 --> 00:17:12,965
My goodness. That's crazy.

346
00:17:12,965 --> 00:17:16,469
- What's going on?
- She was born in 1940. She's 85...

347
00:17:16,469 --> 00:17:17,992
- Really?
- Are you 86 years old?

348
00:17:19,104 --> 00:17:20,866
It's unbelievable.

349
00:17:23,894 --> 00:17:25,811
[Feeling Pleased]

350
00:17:25,811 --> 00:17:27,580
It's warm.

351
00:17:27,580 --> 00:17:29,548
What should we eat?

352
00:17:29,548 --> 00:17:31,984
Americano is a kind of coffee, right?

353
00:17:31,984 --> 00:17:34,386
Let's get two Americanos.

354
00:17:34,386 --> 00:17:36,089
Two Americanos?

355
00:17:37,156 --> 00:17:39,091
We're ready to order.

356
00:17:39,091 --> 00:17:40,246
Okay.

357
00:17:40,826 --> 00:17:42,628
[2 Americanos]
We'll have two Americanos.

358
00:17:42,628 --> 00:17:44,396
Okay, two Americanos.

359
00:17:44,396 --> 00:17:45,731
[1 The Kumquat Forsythia Tart]
One of these.

360
00:17:45,731 --> 00:17:47,032
A kumquat tart?

361
00:17:47,032 --> 00:17:47,933
[1 <i>Bokbunja</i> Madeleine]
One of these.

362
00:17:47,933 --> 00:17:48,934
[1 Peanut Pain Au Chocolat]
One of these as well.

363
00:17:48,934 --> 00:17:52,037
What do you think of our café?
It's pretty, isn't it?

364
00:17:52,037 --> 00:17:53,439
It's very pretty.

365
00:17:53,439 --> 00:17:54,707
- It's so pretty.
- Yes, it is.

366
00:17:54,707 --> 00:17:56,742
- It's lovely.
- It's well-decorated.

367
00:17:56,742 --> 00:18:00,346
This coffee is being made just for you.

368
00:18:00,346 --> 00:18:01,754
- Okay.
- Okay.

369
00:18:02,915 --> 00:18:05,085
- Is this for Table Two?
- Yes.

370
00:18:05,085 --> 00:18:06,452
[On The House From Seon Ho]
As an apology for taking so long,

371
00:18:06,452 --> 00:18:07,853
give them one more
with the <i>bokbunja</i> one.

372
00:18:07,853 --> 00:18:09,722
- Shall I?
- Give it to them on the house.

373
00:18:09,722 --> 00:18:11,924
Tell them it's on you.

374
00:18:11,924 --> 00:18:14,208
It's just like you to think of that.

375
00:18:15,361 --> 00:18:17,997
[Financier On The House]

376
00:18:17,997 --> 00:18:19,865
I should learn from his example.

377
00:18:20,833 --> 00:18:22,501
[2 Americanos, 1 Kumquat Forsythia Tart,
1 <i>Bokbunja</i> Madeleine,]

378
00:18:22,501 --> 00:18:23,903
[1 Peanut Pain Au Chocolat,
1 Financier On The House]

379
00:18:23,903 --> 00:18:25,404
I like that it's not too sweet.

380
00:18:25,404 --> 00:18:27,496
This one's tasty as well.

381
00:18:29,041 --> 00:18:30,109
How is it?

382
00:18:30,109 --> 00:18:32,778
- It's tasty.
- The financier is on the house from Dino.

383
00:18:32,778 --> 00:18:33,812
- For waiting so long.
- It's good.

384
00:18:33,812 --> 00:18:36,315
- It's tasty.
- Thank you.

385
00:18:36,315 --> 00:18:37,216
[Meanwhile, Customers Are Waiting]

386
00:18:37,216 --> 00:18:38,784
- Have a seat.
- Look at the flowers.

387
00:18:38,784 --> 00:18:40,386
Everyone smile!

388
00:18:40,386 --> 00:18:41,587
- All right.
- Okay.

389
00:18:41,587 --> 00:18:43,155
That's it.

390
00:18:43,155 --> 00:18:44,490
Yes, that way.

391
00:18:44,490 --> 00:18:46,892
We're too far away to form a heart.

392
00:18:46,892 --> 00:18:48,928
[A Group Of Six Friends Visiting A Bakery]
You look great. Do another pose.

393
00:18:48,928 --> 00:18:51,230
- Another pose?
- You're in the way.

394
00:18:51,730 --> 00:18:55,000
[And Another Party Of Three]
Sit here.

395
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:57,503
I'm taking the photo now.

396
00:19:00,039 --> 00:19:02,708
[2 Teams Are Waiting
A Party Of 6 And A Party Of 3]

397
00:19:04,076 --> 00:19:06,378
A party of six is waiting
under the name Kim Hyang Ae.

398
00:19:06,845 --> 00:19:09,615
[For The Party Of 6 To Come In]

399
00:19:10,182 --> 00:19:12,751
[We Need The Group Table]

400
00:19:12,751 --> 00:19:13,852
Thank you.

401
00:19:13,852 --> 00:19:17,222
[Only 1 Table For A Party Of 2 Is Available]

402
00:19:18,023 --> 00:19:19,458
- Hee Ae.
- Yes?

403
00:19:19,458 --> 00:19:22,161
I think we can seat
the party of three at the table for two.

404
00:19:22,161 --> 00:19:23,329
- Seat them first?
- Yes.

405
00:19:23,329 --> 00:19:24,530
- Okay.
- I'll bring another chair.

406
00:19:24,530 --> 00:19:26,130
[Seon Ho Handles The Table Turnover]
Okay.

407
00:19:26,732 --> 00:19:30,069
[Table 1 Is Now A Table For 3]

408
00:19:30,536 --> 00:19:32,871
- Jeom Jeom Sun?
- Yes.

409
00:19:32,871 --> 00:19:34,106
- Three people, right?
- Yes.

410
00:19:34,106 --> 00:19:37,142
- We'll seat the party of three first.
- Sure.

411
00:19:37,142 --> 00:19:38,911
Thank you. Here's the menu for you.

412
00:19:38,911 --> 00:19:40,879
- You're Kim Hee Ae.
- Yes.

413
00:19:40,879 --> 00:19:44,177
- It's not often we get to see you.
- Oh, my.

414
00:19:45,250 --> 00:19:46,919
- Hello.
- My goodness.

415
00:19:46,919 --> 00:19:49,288
- She's very famous.
- Hello.

416
00:19:49,288 --> 00:19:51,624
- We appreciate your service.
- Thank you.

417
00:19:51,624 --> 00:19:54,094
- Take your time deciding.
- She came all the way here.

418
00:19:54,094 --> 00:19:55,334
[While Hee Ae Greets The Guests]

419
00:19:58,230 --> 00:20:02,501
[For The Waiting Customers]

420
00:20:05,037 --> 00:20:08,307
[Chan Quickly Gets The Group Table Ready]

421
00:20:14,186 --> 00:20:15,814
- Dino, is it ready?
- Yes.

422
00:20:15,814 --> 00:20:18,784
[The Table Is Ready!]
We have customers waiting.

423
00:20:18,784 --> 00:20:20,185
- Hello.
- It's nice to meet you.

424
00:20:20,185 --> 00:20:23,188
- Take a seat in the room at the back.
- Okay.

425
00:20:23,188 --> 00:20:24,757
- You have coffee, right?
- Coffee?

426
00:20:24,757 --> 00:20:27,157
[Seon Ho Is Busy Taking Orders]
It's at the front of the menu.

427
00:20:27,526 --> 00:20:28,827
[So Chan Handles The Big Group]
Hello.

428
00:20:28,827 --> 00:20:30,429
- Hello.
- Hello.

429
00:20:31,797 --> 00:20:32,765
You're handsome.

430
00:20:32,765 --> 00:20:34,833
Thank you.

431
00:20:34,833 --> 00:20:36,201
You're so good-looking.

432
00:20:36,201 --> 00:20:37,636
Thank you.

433
00:20:38,270 --> 00:20:40,873
- Take your time deciding.
- Okay.

434
00:20:41,607 --> 00:20:44,243
I think you bring in business, Dino.

435
00:20:44,243 --> 00:20:45,244
- Me?
- Yeah.

436
00:20:45,244 --> 00:20:46,745
Yesterday was really quiet.

437
00:20:46,745 --> 00:20:48,000
Really?

438
00:20:48,714 --> 00:20:50,949
Dino brought us good luck.

439
00:20:50,949 --> 00:20:53,552
It's crazy.

440
00:20:54,486 --> 00:20:56,055
- Hey, Dino.
- Yes?

441
00:20:56,055 --> 00:20:58,290
We'd be in trouble without you.

442
00:20:58,290 --> 00:21:00,125
I'd be struggling if you weren't here.

443
00:21:00,125 --> 00:21:02,494
- Can you imagine?
- It's unimaginable.

444
00:21:02,494 --> 00:21:04,096
- Do your parents run a shop?
- When I was young,

445
00:21:04,096 --> 00:21:06,165
they ran a Chinese restaurant,

446
00:21:06,165 --> 00:21:08,367
so I got a bit of experience then.

447
00:21:08,367 --> 00:21:10,402
You're a calm worker.

448
00:21:10,402 --> 00:21:11,904
[You're The Best, Dino]

449
00:21:14,606 --> 00:21:17,710
Dino, you've been too busy
to walk around the area, haven't you?

450
00:21:17,710 --> 00:21:19,244
Well, yes.

451
00:21:19,244 --> 00:21:21,888
That's all the green barley
we use in our desserts.

452
00:21:21,888 --> 00:21:23,082
Is that the green barley?

453
00:21:23,082 --> 00:21:24,583
Yes, that entire field is green barley.

454
00:21:24,583 --> 00:21:27,886
[A Vast Stretch Of Green Barley]

455
00:21:27,886 --> 00:21:30,215
Ki Taek...

456
00:21:30,622 --> 00:21:31,992
- Did he plant it?
- No.

457
00:21:31,992 --> 00:21:33,960
[An Idea Beyond Imagination]

458
00:21:35,661 --> 00:21:38,063
[Clueless Ki Taek]
Yes?

459
00:21:38,063 --> 00:21:41,333
- Ki Taek said they were scallions.
- Oh, scallions.

460
00:21:41,333 --> 00:21:43,001
They turned out to be green barley.

461
00:21:43,001 --> 00:21:45,471
[It's Green Barley, Not Scallions]
I see.

462
00:21:45,471 --> 00:21:47,639
I thought I would show you around

463
00:21:47,639 --> 00:21:49,308
- because we've all been too busy.
- Yeah.

464
00:21:49,308 --> 00:21:52,611
To notice how wonderful this place is.

465
00:21:53,078 --> 00:21:54,546
If you look around...

466
00:21:54,546 --> 00:21:56,081
- Do you see that stone wall path?
- Yes.

467
00:21:56,081 --> 00:21:57,182
It's such a beautiful place,

468
00:21:57,182 --> 00:22:00,018
and the senior residents are warm-hearted.

469
00:22:00,452 --> 00:22:03,226
Isn't it stunning? And the weather's so nice.

470
00:22:06,058 --> 00:22:08,327
- The sky is gorgeous.
- It's unbelievable.

471
00:22:08,327 --> 00:22:10,929
[Recharged After A Quick Break]

472
00:22:11,930 --> 00:22:13,398
Let's do a good job!

473
00:22:13,398 --> 00:22:14,733
- Yes, Chef.
- Let's do a good job.

474
00:22:14,733 --> 00:22:16,602
- Hee Ae's here.
- Okay.

475
00:22:16,602 --> 00:22:18,470
[The Manager And The Loaf Of Bread]
Extra care is needed for the bread loaf.

476
00:22:18,470 --> 00:22:19,738
Yes, Chef!

477
00:22:19,738 --> 00:22:22,341
[The King Of Baking Is On The Edge]

478
00:22:22,341 --> 00:22:24,543
[The Start Of The Incident First Meeting]

479
00:22:29,148 --> 00:22:32,551
[The First Taste Test
Of The King Of Baking's Bread Loaf]

480
00:22:33,585 --> 00:22:35,053
How is it?

481
00:22:35,053 --> 00:22:37,156
Did you not use any butter?

482
00:22:37,156 --> 00:22:38,390
I did.

483
00:22:38,390 --> 00:22:39,417
- You did?
- Yes.

484
00:22:39,417 --> 00:22:41,126
I can definitely smell it but...

485
00:22:41,126 --> 00:22:42,460
But?

486
00:22:43,128 --> 00:22:45,230
I can't really taste it.

487
00:22:45,230 --> 00:22:46,465
It tastes a bit plain.

488
00:22:46,465 --> 00:22:49,134
[Something Is Missing]

489
00:22:49,134 --> 00:22:52,238
They say butter isn't that bad.
It's good for you.

490
00:22:52,238 --> 00:22:53,806
Let's add plenty of it.

491
00:22:53,806 --> 00:22:55,007
[Strongly Recommends More Butter]

492
00:22:55,007 --> 00:22:56,475
It will make it even more delicious.

493
00:22:56,475 --> 00:22:57,376
[Lightheaded]

494
00:22:57,376 --> 00:22:58,498
Sure.

495
00:22:59,311 --> 00:23:01,480
- We need to consume salt.
- Listen.

496
00:23:01,480 --> 00:23:04,383
Can't we use this much butter?

497
00:23:04,383 --> 00:23:05,284
[This Is How The Nightmare Began]

498
00:23:05,284 --> 00:23:07,920
[The Second Taste Test]
The salt also...

499
00:23:07,920 --> 00:23:11,924
It still needs to rise a little more.

500
00:23:13,125 --> 00:23:14,226
Is it better than last time?

501
00:23:14,226 --> 00:23:15,899
I think the texture's better.

502
00:23:16,829 --> 00:23:18,388
What do you think?

503
00:23:19,231 --> 00:23:20,599
Are you still not satisfied?

504
00:23:20,599 --> 00:23:22,501
She's not satisfied.

505
00:23:22,501 --> 00:23:24,570
[Ki Taek Quickly Tries A Taste]
She doesn't look happy.

506
00:23:24,570 --> 00:23:26,605
- We need to redo it.
- That's not it.

507
00:23:26,605 --> 00:23:29,074
It tastes like a normal loaf of bread.

508
00:23:29,074 --> 00:23:31,243
It's just that I'm thinking of...

509
00:23:31,243 --> 00:23:35,147
[Failed To Satisfy The Manager Again]
You want something a lot more buttery.

510
00:23:35,147 --> 00:23:37,149
This is more of a plain bread.

511
00:23:38,023 --> 00:23:40,619
It's good for everyday eating.

512
00:23:40,619 --> 00:23:41,820
[French Loaf]
It's good.

513
00:23:41,820 --> 00:23:44,022
[Made For Everyday Meals
With Minimal Butter And Sugar]

514
00:23:44,022 --> 00:23:45,287
Yeah, it's fine.

515
00:23:46,959 --> 00:23:48,427
It is whatever.

516
00:23:48,427 --> 00:23:49,728
[His Pride's Deflated]

517
00:23:49,728 --> 00:23:51,145
Don't lose heart.

518
00:23:52,364 --> 00:23:54,833
The loaf of bread is coming out today.

519
00:23:54,833 --> 00:23:56,635
- At last?
- Yes.

520
00:23:56,635 --> 00:23:58,470
We changed it a bit, Hee Ae.

521
00:23:58,470 --> 00:23:59,972
- It's more-
- It's a new recipe?

522
00:23:59,972 --> 00:24:03,508
- Yes, it's now a bit more...
- You adjusted the ratio?

523
00:24:03,508 --> 00:24:04,843
We added a bit more butter.

524
00:24:04,843 --> 00:24:06,378
- Okay.
- You need to sample it.

525
00:24:06,378 --> 00:24:07,446
- Cha Loaf Bread.
- I'm excited.

526
00:24:07,446 --> 00:24:08,780
[Cha Loaf Bread Is Back]

527
00:24:08,780 --> 00:24:11,984
[New And Improved
Based On The Manager's Feedback]

528
00:24:12,784 --> 00:24:16,021
[It's Back With A Deeper Flavor]

529
00:24:16,922 --> 00:24:19,691
[A Rich Flavor In Every Bite]

530
00:24:20,959 --> 00:24:23,095
[Cha Loaf Bread Is Coming Right Up]

531
00:24:23,095 --> 00:24:24,596
[It's Extra Buttery]

532
00:24:25,280 --> 00:24:28,934
[Dough Prep In Full Swing]
Let's put in more butter.

533
00:24:30,903 --> 00:24:34,539
[Extra Butter For A Richer Flavor]

534
00:24:35,674 --> 00:24:38,410
[Let's Not Hold Back]

535
00:24:38,977 --> 00:24:43,348
[Honey Locks In Moisture,
Making The Loaf More Tender]

536
00:24:43,348 --> 00:24:44,816
Set this to four minutes.

537
00:24:44,816 --> 00:24:45,984
- Four minutes?
- That's right.

538
00:24:45,984 --> 00:24:47,619
[Proof For 70 Minutes For A Moist Loaf]

539
00:24:56,228 --> 00:24:59,231
[The King Of Baking Shows Us How It's Done]

540
00:25:00,032 --> 00:25:02,868
[Roll Out The Dough
With A Rolling Pin To Degas It]

541
00:25:03,535 --> 00:25:05,637
[Popping Air Bubbles]

542
00:25:09,100 --> 00:25:13,138
[Fold The Sides In So They Overlap,
Then Roll The Dough Out Flat]

543
00:25:13,812 --> 00:25:15,747
[Grab The Corners And Pinch Gently]

544
00:25:15,747 --> 00:25:17,683
[Repeat A Second Time]

545
00:25:17,683 --> 00:25:19,851
[Repeat A Third Time]

546
00:25:19,851 --> 00:25:22,821
[Finish By Pinching The Seam Closed]

547
00:25:24,556 --> 00:25:26,625
[Two Pieces Come Together To Form A Loaf]

548
00:25:26,625 --> 00:25:28,026
Okay, it's your turn.

549
00:25:28,026 --> 00:25:29,170
Okay.

550
00:25:30,963 --> 00:25:35,000
[It's Time For Ki Taek To Practice]

551
00:25:37,602 --> 00:25:40,005
[He Does As He Was Taught,
One Step At A Time]

552
00:25:40,472 --> 00:25:43,208
How can you handle this pressure?

553
00:25:43,208 --> 00:25:44,609
All the cameras are on you.

554
00:25:44,609 --> 00:25:48,480
[Ki Taek Cam 1, 2, 3]

555
00:25:48,480 --> 00:25:50,082
[Ki Taek Cam 1]

556
00:25:50,082 --> 00:25:52,184
[Ki Taek Cam 2]

557
00:25:52,184 --> 00:25:54,386
[Ki Taek Cam 3]

558
00:25:54,386 --> 00:25:56,154
Should I roll it a bit more?

559
00:25:56,154 --> 00:25:57,756
[Under The King Of Baking's Wing]
Press gently.

560
00:25:57,756 --> 00:26:00,125
Roll it out.

561
00:26:00,125 --> 00:26:03,128
[Ki Taek Is Rapidly Improving]

562
00:26:03,128 --> 00:26:05,197
You're pretty good at this.

563
00:26:05,197 --> 00:26:08,834
I learned this before. I've had practice.

564
00:26:08,834 --> 00:26:10,402
Do you think I'm doing okay?

565
00:26:10,402 --> 00:26:12,070
- I'm so impressed right now.
- Really?

566
00:26:12,070 --> 00:26:14,506
I'm hardly an expert,
but to me it seems like

567
00:26:14,506 --> 00:26:16,240
you're doing an impressive job.

568
00:26:17,309 --> 00:26:19,444
What? You're doing awesome.

569
00:26:19,444 --> 00:26:20,879
[Impressive Ki Taek]
I mean it.

570
00:26:21,446 --> 00:26:25,417
[Ki Taek's Heart Is Rising Like The Dough]

571
00:26:26,184 --> 00:26:28,067
It rose nicely.

572
00:26:29,388 --> 00:26:31,823
I made sure it rose properly

573
00:26:31,823 --> 00:26:34,398
by staring it down like this.

574
00:26:35,527 --> 00:26:37,062
- You pressured it?
- Yes.

575
00:26:37,062 --> 00:26:38,942
[A Loaf That Rose Under Pressure]
Stared it down.

576
00:26:40,999 --> 00:26:42,968
I just care so much.

577
00:26:42,968 --> 00:26:44,269
I care a lot.

578
00:26:44,269 --> 00:26:45,804
[It's Because I Care]

579
00:26:49,641 --> 00:26:52,244
[Brush With Egg Wash
For A Golden Color And Glossy Finish]

580
00:26:56,982 --> 00:26:58,350
[Standing Awkwardly]

581
00:26:58,350 --> 00:27:00,018
- Why?
- Can I get... Okay.

582
00:27:00,018 --> 00:27:01,486
Should I just get some like this?

583
00:27:01,486 --> 00:27:02,721
[Just Dip]

584
00:27:03,522 --> 00:27:05,457
What should I do?

585
00:27:06,024 --> 00:27:07,610
He's so cute.

586
00:27:10,729 --> 00:27:11,836
Thank you.

587
00:27:11,836 --> 00:27:13,818
- That's plenty, right?
- Yes.

588
00:27:14,633 --> 00:27:17,702
- I was very generous.
- Thank you.

589
00:27:18,276 --> 00:27:21,345
[May It Soak Up The Egg Wash
And Turn Golden Brown]

590
00:27:23,075 --> 00:27:24,342
Let me take a look.

591
00:27:24,342 --> 00:27:25,544
- We're good.
- Okay.

592
00:27:25,544 --> 00:27:27,446
[The Finished Dough Goes Into The Oven]

593
00:27:28,113 --> 00:27:32,484
[This Is The Sound Of Cha Loaf Bread
Rising Deliciously]

594
00:27:32,951 --> 00:27:34,553
[30 Minutes Later]

595
00:27:34,553 --> 00:27:36,775
I'll take it out now.

596
00:27:45,797 --> 00:27:47,732
It looks great.

597
00:27:47,732 --> 00:27:49,468
Look at that rise.

598
00:27:49,468 --> 00:27:50,969
It has risen beautifully.

599
00:27:52,804 --> 00:27:54,874
The King of Baking.

600
00:27:57,909 --> 00:28:00,479
[The King Of Clowning Around]

601
00:28:05,550 --> 00:28:08,453
I wanted to try it
when Chef Cha wasn't around

602
00:28:08,453 --> 00:28:09,754
because I knew he'd scold me.

603
00:28:09,754 --> 00:28:11,857
[Ki Taek's Secret Kitchen Shenanigans]

604
00:28:14,693 --> 00:28:17,229
[Jung Chun Ja Third Visit]

605
00:28:18,163 --> 00:28:19,598
[Seon Ho Spots The Familiar Customer]

606
00:28:19,598 --> 00:28:22,834
[And Rushes Out To Greet Her]

607
00:28:22,834 --> 00:28:24,169
Hello.

608
00:28:25,003 --> 00:28:26,905
- Where are you going?
- I came here to buy bread.

609
00:28:26,905 --> 00:28:28,240
Oh, you came to buy bread?

610
00:28:28,240 --> 00:28:29,641
- Don't you have any?
- Of course, we do.

611
00:28:29,641 --> 00:28:31,576
What type of bread did you want?

612
00:28:31,576 --> 00:28:32,611
I need to see what there is.

613
00:28:32,611 --> 00:28:35,147
[Let Me Park First]
Yes, you should take a look.

614
00:28:35,147 --> 00:28:36,988
She's parking first.

615
00:28:38,316 --> 00:28:39,551
I need to see before I decide.

616
00:28:39,551 --> 00:28:41,319
[Hand-In-Hand]

617
00:28:41,953 --> 00:28:43,955
[Chuckles]

618
00:28:43,955 --> 00:28:45,423
I need to look around.

619
00:28:45,423 --> 00:28:47,459
Lean on me for support.

620
00:28:49,427 --> 00:28:50,421
What's this?

621
00:28:50,421 --> 00:28:51,830
[Peanut Pain Au Chocolat]
That one's delicious.

622
00:28:51,830 --> 00:28:53,031
It's very tasty.

623
00:28:53,031 --> 00:28:54,799
- I'll take four of them.
- Four? Okay.

624
00:28:54,799 --> 00:28:57,269
[Takeout Order :
4 Bonjour Peanut Pain Au Chocolat]

625
00:28:57,269 --> 00:29:00,539
[Our Regular Customers
Are Ordering More Than Usual]

626
00:29:00,539 --> 00:29:02,101
[It's Heavier Than Usual]

627
00:29:02,101 --> 00:29:04,134
I'll carry it over there for you.

628
00:29:12,551 --> 00:29:14,401
Ma'am, your ride is here.

629
00:29:15,086 --> 00:29:16,588
Why are there two bags?

630
00:29:16,588 --> 00:29:19,391
We wrapped them separately.

631
00:29:19,391 --> 00:29:21,393
[She Can't Help But Smile]

632
00:29:21,393 --> 00:29:22,716
Be careful.

633
00:29:23,395 --> 00:29:25,162
- Thank you.
- Sure.

634
00:29:26,031 --> 00:29:27,265
The loaf of bread will be ready later.

635
00:29:27,265 --> 00:29:29,525
Come by then if you need some.

636
00:29:30,402 --> 00:29:32,837
- I'll buy a lot since you're closing.
- You'll buy a lot?

637
00:29:32,837 --> 00:29:35,307
What a shame we're closing today, right?

638
00:29:35,307 --> 00:29:37,342
- Thank you.
- Now that you're leaving,

639
00:29:37,342 --> 00:29:40,545
take care of yourself,
and come back again sometime.

640
00:29:40,545 --> 00:29:43,248
- Okay.
- You're not sure you'll come back?

641
00:29:43,248 --> 00:29:44,749
I'll definitely come back.

642
00:29:44,749 --> 00:29:46,580
Yes, come back.

643
00:29:47,452 --> 00:29:49,321
- Thank you, ma'am.
- Sure.

644
00:30:01,866 --> 00:30:05,937
I really think I will miss you so much.

645
00:30:05,937 --> 00:30:07,772
You're so cute.

646
00:30:07,772 --> 00:30:09,307
- Who is?
- You!

647
00:30:09,307 --> 00:30:10,475
- I'm talking about you.
- Oh, please.

648
00:30:10,475 --> 00:30:13,378
- I'm just an old lady.
- Nonsense!

649
00:30:13,378 --> 00:30:15,947
You're still so pretty.

650
00:30:15,947 --> 00:30:18,750
When I was young,
I was often told I was pretty.

651
00:30:18,750 --> 00:30:21,920
People said I was so beautiful and petite.

652
00:30:21,920 --> 00:30:24,089
- Do you want some Korean melon?
- That's okay.

653
00:30:24,089 --> 00:30:26,591
- You should have some.
- No, I'm fine.

654
00:30:26,591 --> 00:30:28,118
Here.

655
00:30:29,227 --> 00:30:31,663
Drink this. It's refreshing.

656
00:30:33,064 --> 00:30:35,667
In this village,

657
00:30:35,667 --> 00:30:37,502
we all share what we have

658
00:30:37,502 --> 00:30:39,471
and help each other out.

659
00:30:39,471 --> 00:30:42,674
I give to others,
and I also receive from them.

660
00:30:42,674 --> 00:30:45,810
You need to treat others with kindness.

661
00:30:45,810 --> 00:30:49,007
It's no good being cold to each other.

662
00:30:50,615 --> 00:30:54,419
<i>I've enjoyed how lively it's been.</i>

663
00:30:54,419 --> 00:30:57,589
<i>Food tastes better when you eat together.</i>

664
00:30:58,723 --> 00:31:00,458
Next time,

665
00:31:00,458 --> 00:31:03,728
if you come again...

666
00:31:03,728 --> 00:31:05,130
Will you not come back?

667
00:31:05,130 --> 00:31:06,971
Come again.

668
00:31:16,441 --> 00:31:19,344
[Time For A Quick Quiz]

669
00:31:19,344 --> 00:31:21,179
I'll just do this first.

670
00:31:21,179 --> 00:31:23,114
[After A Busy Rush]

671
00:31:23,114 --> 00:31:27,385
[Seon Ho Cuts Into His Saved Croissant]

672
00:31:27,385 --> 00:31:29,988
[What Do You Think
Our Golden Part-Timer Chan Said To Him?]

673
00:31:29,988 --> 00:31:31,890
- Let's eat this, Chan.
- Okay.

674
00:31:31,890 --> 00:31:34,859
- Should I make you a coffee?
- No, I'm fine.

675
00:31:35,927 --> 00:31:37,595
- Want to try it?
- I'll try as your student.

676
00:31:37,595 --> 00:31:39,664
Can you make me an iced Americano?

677
00:31:39,664 --> 00:31:41,066
- I'll try my best.
- Okay.

678
00:31:41,066 --> 00:31:43,902
I feel like I can count on you.

679
00:31:43,902 --> 00:31:47,205
[The Student Makes A Coffee For His Teacher]

680
00:31:47,205 --> 00:31:50,642
[Locking It In From 8 To 6 O'clock
Just As He Was Taught]

681
00:32:06,324 --> 00:32:08,326
[Seon Ho Seems Busy]

682
00:32:08,993 --> 00:32:11,363
[Leave It Where He Walks By Often]

683
00:32:12,364 --> 00:32:13,965
- Oh, man.
- Eat up.

684
00:32:13,965 --> 00:32:15,266
We weren't this busy earlier.

685
00:32:15,266 --> 00:32:16,266
[Seon Ho Is Back.]

686
00:32:17,802 --> 00:32:20,271
[He Takes A Bite Of The Croissant]

687
00:32:20,271 --> 00:32:24,142
[And A Sip Of His Student's Coffee]

688
00:32:27,779 --> 00:32:28,880
Dino.

689
00:32:28,880 --> 00:32:31,449
I'll leave the coffee to you from now on.

690
00:32:31,449 --> 00:32:33,784
No, you need to stay by my side today.

691
00:32:35,556 --> 00:32:39,760
[Thanks To His Fast-Learning Student]

692
00:32:41,025 --> 00:32:42,927
[Seon Ho Can Stop Making Coffee]

693
00:32:42,927 --> 00:32:44,996
[And Focus On Other Things]

694
00:32:44,996 --> 00:32:48,133
This was made personally
by the actor Cha Seung Won.

695
00:32:48,533 --> 00:32:50,402
She's coming in.
I'd better wrap up the bread.

696
00:32:50,402 --> 00:32:51,770
Hang on. The loaf of bread...

697
00:32:51,770 --> 00:32:54,072
[The Loaf Of Bread]

698
00:32:54,072 --> 00:32:58,076
[Available From 1 p.m.
Limited To 5 Loaves]

699
00:32:58,076 --> 00:33:00,879
[It Is Now One O'clock]

700
00:33:00,879 --> 00:33:02,680
- One loaf of bread.
- Okay.

701
00:33:02,680 --> 00:33:04,783
- I'll put one aside for you.
- Okay.

702
00:33:04,783 --> 00:33:06,151
There's a limited amount.

703
00:33:06,151 --> 00:33:07,654
[To Make Our Customer Happy]

704
00:33:07,654 --> 00:33:11,589
[By Ensuring She Gets
One Of The Five Loaves]

705
00:33:11,589 --> 00:33:14,893
[Seon Ho The Bread Man Acts Quickly]

706
00:33:15,994 --> 00:33:17,996
[She's Here For Her Reserved Loaf]
Welcome.

707
00:33:17,996 --> 00:33:19,063
I came for the loaf of bread.

708
00:33:19,063 --> 00:33:20,165
Oh, right!

709
00:33:20,165 --> 00:33:21,666
He's getting it ready for you.

710
00:33:22,434 --> 00:33:23,768
Take a seat.

711
00:33:23,768 --> 00:33:25,770
[Our Golden Part-Timer Offers Her A Chair]

712
00:33:25,770 --> 00:33:27,439
- Would you like some water?
- What?

713
00:33:27,439 --> 00:33:29,040
- I've had some.
- You have? Okay.

714
00:33:29,040 --> 00:33:30,708
[After A Short Wait]

715
00:33:31,609 --> 00:33:32,944
[The Bread Man Appears]
Ma'am!

716
00:33:32,944 --> 00:33:35,307
This is fresh from the oven.

717
00:33:35,914 --> 00:33:37,415
It's still warm,

718
00:33:37,415 --> 00:33:40,531
so if you seal the top,
the bread will get too moist,

719
00:33:40,531 --> 00:33:43,521
- so take it home with the top open.
- Okay.

720
00:33:43,521 --> 00:33:44,722
Air it out a bit.

721
00:33:44,722 --> 00:33:47,358
- I've paid you, right?
- You paid me earlier.

722
00:33:47,358 --> 00:33:49,294
It's all paid for, ma'am.

723
00:33:49,994 --> 00:33:51,162
Ma'am.

724
00:33:51,162 --> 00:33:53,498
Thank you!

725
00:33:55,066 --> 00:33:56,234
Ma'am.

726
00:33:58,636 --> 00:34:00,839
Thank you.

727
00:34:00,839 --> 00:34:01,873
I've spent a lot here.

728
00:34:01,873 --> 00:34:03,074
I know!

729
00:34:04,409 --> 00:34:06,344
- Thank you.
- Take care.

730
00:34:07,111 --> 00:34:09,180
Be careful. Watch your step.

731
00:34:11,282 --> 00:34:13,451
This lovely bread won't fall over, right?

732
00:34:13,451 --> 00:34:15,253
It won't.

733
00:34:15,253 --> 00:34:16,321
Thank you.

734
00:34:16,321 --> 00:34:19,090
- Cha Seung Won made that himself.
- Okay.

735
00:34:21,893 --> 00:34:22,961
[Loaf Of Bread Sales Log Reserved]

736
00:34:22,961 --> 00:34:25,730
[Sold - Kim Sun Ja]

737
00:34:27,399 --> 00:34:28,466
All right.

738
00:34:28,466 --> 00:34:30,468
[Another Customer Is Here]
Hello, ma'am. What brings you here?

739
00:34:30,468 --> 00:34:32,437
- The loaf of bread.
- The loaf of bread.

740
00:34:32,971 --> 00:34:34,606
You're here.

741
00:34:34,606 --> 00:34:35,874
[Park Bong Ja - Very First Customer]

742
00:34:35,874 --> 00:34:38,977
You're really dedicated workers.

743
00:34:40,144 --> 00:34:41,913
It's freshly baked, so it's still warm.

744
00:34:41,913 --> 00:34:44,415
It will get too moist if you seal the top,

745
00:34:44,415 --> 00:34:46,150
- so take it home like this.
- Thank you.

746
00:34:48,019 --> 00:34:50,522
Thank you for coming.

747
00:34:53,191 --> 00:34:55,460
- Thank you.
- Get home safely.

748
00:34:58,162 --> 00:34:59,364
[Loaf Of Bread Sales Log]

749
00:34:59,364 --> 00:35:00,498
[Sold - Park Bong Ja]

750
00:35:00,498 --> 00:35:03,301
[Sold - Group Of Customers]

751
00:35:03,301 --> 00:35:06,971
Our male staff are so handsome and polite.

752
00:35:06,971 --> 00:35:08,940
- Dino.
- It's no wonder business is thriving.

753
00:35:08,940 --> 00:35:09,974
Dino.

754
00:35:09,974 --> 00:35:12,176
[Rambling Out Of Awkwardness]
Is it all good, Dino?

755
00:35:12,777 --> 00:35:14,249
Welcome.

756
00:35:15,713 --> 00:35:17,215
Hello!

757
00:35:17,782 --> 00:35:19,617
- You can come this way.
- This way, please.

758
00:35:19,617 --> 00:35:22,053
- There's no bread.
- Which bread?

759
00:35:22,053 --> 00:35:23,454
- The loaf of bread?
- Yes.

760
00:35:23,454 --> 00:35:25,290
Well, the thing is...

761
00:35:26,224 --> 00:35:27,792
[There's One Left]
You came separately, right?

762
00:35:27,792 --> 00:35:29,694
[But They Both Want One]
In that case...

763
00:35:29,694 --> 00:35:32,430
There isn't enough
for you to take one each.

764
00:35:32,430 --> 00:35:33,998
They're out of bread.

765
00:35:33,998 --> 00:35:35,567
- They're all out?
- They're out of bread.

766
00:35:35,567 --> 00:35:38,002
I guess we'd better go.

767
00:35:38,570 --> 00:35:39,638
[The Bread Man Thinks For A Moment]

768
00:35:39,638 --> 00:35:41,406
Wait, I...

769
00:35:41,406 --> 00:35:42,876
There's one loaf...

770
00:35:42,876 --> 00:35:44,244
Ma'am!

771
00:35:44,742 --> 00:35:46,945
Are you planning to park inside?

772
00:35:46,945 --> 00:35:48,212
There's no bread, so I'm leaving.

773
00:35:48,212 --> 00:35:49,681
No, we do have some.

774
00:35:49,681 --> 00:35:51,916
[Rushing Out To Catch Customers]
There's bread in the back.

775
00:35:51,916 --> 00:35:53,651
- We have bread.
- You do?

776
00:35:53,651 --> 00:35:56,187
- I can give you one each.
- You're sure?

777
00:35:56,187 --> 00:35:58,339
- You don't have one?
- We have some.

778
00:36:00,458 --> 00:36:03,194
[She Trusts The Bread Man
And Makes A U-Turn]

779
00:36:03,194 --> 00:36:05,997
If you have bread, I'd better wait here.

780
00:36:05,997 --> 00:36:08,399
- You want me to sit back down?
- Yes.

781
00:36:09,534 --> 00:36:11,703
Excuse me, Chef.

782
00:36:12,704 --> 00:36:13,972
Yes?

783
00:36:13,972 --> 00:36:16,641
The loaf is so popular,
we decided to sell it in halves.

784
00:36:16,641 --> 00:36:17,942
- Half?
- Cut it in half for me.

785
00:36:17,942 --> 00:36:19,170
- Just half?
- Yeah.

786
00:36:19,170 --> 00:36:21,579
- I'm giving two seniors one slice each,
- All right.

787
00:36:21,579 --> 00:36:23,681
[Doing Their Best]
so it needs to be evenly divided.

788
00:36:23,681 --> 00:36:24,849
[So No One Leaves Empty-Handed]

789
00:36:24,849 --> 00:36:26,050
Look at you.

790
00:36:26,050 --> 00:36:28,286
You've really improved.

791
00:36:28,987 --> 00:36:31,489
- Have I improved?
- Yes, a lot.

792
00:36:31,489 --> 00:36:32,900
Your work speaks for itself.

793
00:36:33,460 --> 00:36:36,027
[Skillfully Cut By Chef Taek]

794
00:36:36,027 --> 00:36:40,431
[A Half-Loaf For Each Customer]
Ma'am. It's freshly baked. Carry it like this.

795
00:36:40,431 --> 00:36:41,899
Here's your loaf of bread.

796
00:36:41,899 --> 00:36:43,034
I gave each of you half a loaf,

797
00:36:43,034 --> 00:36:44,836
so I only charged you 2,000 won each.

798
00:36:44,836 --> 00:36:46,938
- Ma'am, do you want to take this?
- What?

799
00:36:46,938 --> 00:36:49,273
[A Canvas Bag For Takeaway Orders]
Do you want this?

800
00:36:49,273 --> 00:36:51,409
- Sure, give me one.
- I'll give you one each.

801
00:36:51,409 --> 00:36:53,144
I'll take it if you want.

802
00:36:54,946 --> 00:36:56,948
It's so cheap.

803
00:36:56,948 --> 00:36:58,783
- It's cheap.
- Right?

804
00:36:58,783 --> 00:37:00,885
But the quality of the bread...

805
00:37:00,885 --> 00:37:02,654
- Is it good?
- It's delicious.

806
00:37:02,654 --> 00:37:04,489
- It's delicious?
- Yes.

807
00:37:04,489 --> 00:37:06,591
What's with all this bread today?

808
00:37:06,591 --> 00:37:08,192
Today?

809
00:37:08,192 --> 00:37:09,794
It's because today is the last day.

810
00:37:09,794 --> 00:37:11,095
- I heard that.
- Yes.

811
00:37:11,095 --> 00:37:12,830
If you have to go, you have to go.

812
00:37:12,830 --> 00:37:14,247
I feel a bit sad.

813
00:37:15,333 --> 00:37:16,701
There's only one left.

814
00:37:16,701 --> 00:37:19,170
[Today's The Last Day?]

815
00:37:22,707 --> 00:37:25,476
Can I also have 10,000 won worth of these?

816
00:37:25,476 --> 00:37:27,512
- Sorry?
- Can I get 10,000 won worth of these?

817
00:37:27,512 --> 00:37:29,781
- You want 10,000 won worth? Sure.
- Of course.

818
00:37:29,781 --> 00:37:31,683
- It's possible?
- Yes.

819
00:37:31,683 --> 00:37:33,451
So, 10,000 won worth...

820
00:37:33,451 --> 00:37:35,653
Let's see. Pain au chocolat, croissant...

821
00:37:35,653 --> 00:37:37,522
- How about one of each?
- Yes, give me one each.

822
00:37:37,522 --> 00:37:39,791
- All right.
- I'll take one of each.

823
00:37:39,791 --> 00:37:42,894
This financier is on the house.

824
00:37:49,240 --> 00:37:51,903
- Enjoy.
- Thank you.

825
00:37:51,903 --> 00:37:54,172
You'll carry it back in that, right?

826
00:37:54,172 --> 00:37:56,174
- Come here.
- Valet parking.

827
00:37:57,008 --> 00:37:59,544
[Hand-In-Hand Escort Service]
Let's go to the parking lot.

828
00:37:59,544 --> 00:38:01,679
- This one? Should I put it in here?
- Yes.

829
00:38:01,679 --> 00:38:02,780
- Okay.
- Be careful.

830
00:38:02,780 --> 00:38:03,981
It's so convenient.

831
00:38:03,981 --> 00:38:05,383
Put it in here?

832
00:38:05,383 --> 00:38:06,718
- Thank you.
- Sure.

833
00:38:06,718 --> 00:38:08,786
- Come again this afternoon.
- Come again.

834
00:38:08,786 --> 00:38:11,158
Come by even if you don't want to eat.

835
00:38:11,158 --> 00:38:12,642
Just come for a stroll.

836
00:38:14,092 --> 00:38:15,927
- Thank you.
- Get home safely.

837
00:38:15,927 --> 00:38:17,361
Bye.

838
00:38:17,361 --> 00:38:19,430
They're so sweet.

839
00:38:19,430 --> 00:38:21,265
- Aren't they so lovely?
- They're lovely.

840
00:38:21,265 --> 00:38:22,519
They're so sweet.

841
00:38:23,334 --> 00:38:25,937
[After The Unexpected Sale Of Half-Loaves]

842
00:38:26,337 --> 00:38:28,639
- Those half-loaves were a great idea.
- Right?

843
00:38:28,639 --> 00:38:30,041
- You cut it, right?
- Yes, we cut it

844
00:38:30,041 --> 00:38:32,610
- so they could get one.
- What a great move.

845
00:38:32,610 --> 00:38:33,511
I asked Ki Taek to do it.

846
00:38:33,511 --> 00:38:35,313
- I did well, right?
- Yes.

847
00:38:35,780 --> 00:38:37,749
- Well done.
- This is how you get a compliment.

848
00:38:37,749 --> 00:38:39,250
You did so well.

849
00:38:40,451 --> 00:38:42,232
The loaf of bread is very popular.

850
00:38:42,232 --> 00:38:45,656
Yes, senior ladies want
something that keeps well.

851
00:38:45,656 --> 00:38:47,125
- I see.
- Yes, like the rolls.

852
00:38:47,125 --> 00:38:50,695
Does that mean I can't try the loaf?

853
00:38:50,695 --> 00:38:52,393
Oh, no!

854
00:38:53,190 --> 00:38:56,701
Tell him to set one aside.

855
00:38:56,701 --> 00:38:59,270
[Unfortunately]

856
00:38:59,270 --> 00:39:03,040
[The Last Loaf Is Already Reserved]

857
00:39:04,242 --> 00:39:07,145
[And The Creator Of The Cha Loaf Bread]

858
00:39:07,145 --> 00:39:08,446
[Is Busy Preparing Lunch]

859
00:39:08,446 --> 00:39:13,417
Cha Chef is a really complicated person.

860
00:39:13,417 --> 00:39:16,220
He can be very gruff one second,

861
00:39:16,220 --> 00:39:18,556
- and a clown the next.
- The King of Baking!

862
00:39:18,556 --> 00:39:23,327
But he's also selfless with his cooking.

863
00:39:23,327 --> 00:39:26,631
He can make something simple on his own,

864
00:39:26,631 --> 00:39:30,101
but he goes and cooks for everyone.

865
00:39:30,101 --> 00:39:33,604
I think he has multiple personalities.

866
00:39:35,807 --> 00:39:37,742
- Which one is really him?
- Seriously.

867
00:39:39,243 --> 00:39:42,346
[12:30 p.m.]

868
00:39:43,481 --> 00:39:44,649
- It's 12:30 p.m.?
- Yes.

869
00:39:44,649 --> 00:39:47,385
I don't have time to be doing this.

870
00:39:47,385 --> 00:39:50,988
[Loud Banging]

871
00:39:50,988 --> 00:39:55,493
[What Is This Noise?]

872
00:39:57,728 --> 00:40:02,066
[It's The Sound Of Chef Cha Making <i>Yukjeon</i>!]

873
00:40:03,467 --> 00:40:06,771
[Removing Excess Blood From The Beef]

874
00:40:41,742 --> 00:40:47,748
[It Goes Gently Onto The Heated Pan]

875
00:40:55,786 --> 00:40:57,555
- Ki Taek.
- Yes?

876
00:40:57,555 --> 00:41:00,524
- Lower it to medium heat.
- Okay.

877
00:41:00,524 --> 00:41:06,864
[Precise Heat Control
Is The Key To A Tasty <i>Yukjeon</i>]

878
00:41:06,864 --> 00:41:10,468
[Golden Brown]

879
00:41:30,521 --> 00:41:35,693
<i>[Tteokguk</i> To Enjoy With The <i>Yukjeon</i>]

880
00:41:35,693 --> 00:41:39,030
[A Jeolla-Style Meal :
Start With <i>Yukjeon</i>, Finish With <i>Tteokguk</i>]

881
00:41:39,030 --> 00:41:40,100
[A Rich Beef-Bone Broth]

882
00:41:40,100 --> 00:41:45,472
[Topped With Freshly Sliced Scallions]

883
00:41:48,806 --> 00:41:51,809
[Add Plenty Of Rice Cakes (<i>Tteok</i>)]

884
00:41:51,809 --> 00:41:56,414
[Stir-Fry The Garnish For The <i>Tteokguk</i>]

885
00:42:02,553 --> 00:42:04,777
- Ki Taek, whenever you have time,
- Yes?

886
00:42:05,959 --> 00:42:09,193
- Since we need to set the table anyway.
- Yes.

887
00:42:09,193 --> 00:42:11,329
Do it with your free hand.

888
00:42:11,329 --> 00:42:13,664
- With your right hand?
- Your free hand.

889
00:42:13,664 --> 00:42:15,266
- You're free right now.
- Got it.

890
00:42:17,335 --> 00:42:19,437
- Should we set the table as well?
- Yes, take out that kimchi.

891
00:42:19,437 --> 00:42:20,638
That's the one.

892
00:42:20,638 --> 00:42:23,574
- That's the one we got from our customer.
- Kimchi and...

893
00:42:23,574 --> 00:42:25,242
That's all we need.

894
00:42:25,242 --> 00:42:26,651
- Okay.
- All right.

895
00:42:37,369 --> 00:42:38,402
[A Quick Trip To The Hall]

896
00:42:38,402 --> 00:42:39,724
Have you finished here?

897
00:42:39,724 --> 00:42:41,692
Which item was most popular today?

898
00:42:41,692 --> 00:42:44,962
The customers were raving about the loaf.

899
00:42:44,962 --> 00:42:46,631
The Cha Loaf Bread was a huge hit.

900
00:42:46,631 --> 00:42:48,633
- This is Chef Cha.
- Hello.

901
00:42:48,633 --> 00:42:51,069
- Hello.
- He baked the bread.

902
00:42:51,069 --> 00:42:52,804
- The loaf of bread was delicious.
- Was it?

903
00:42:52,804 --> 00:42:53,838
- Yes.
- Good.

904
00:42:53,838 --> 00:42:55,873
You should have made more. It was so good.

905
00:42:55,873 --> 00:42:57,208
It's too hard.

906
00:42:57,208 --> 00:42:58,876
- Is it hard to make?
- Yes.

907
00:42:58,876 --> 00:43:01,415
We can only make a limited number.

908
00:43:01,415 --> 00:43:03,948
I need to make the dough and let it rise.

909
00:43:03,948 --> 00:43:05,750
[Letting Out Their Struggles]
so it turns out really tasty,

910
00:43:05,750 --> 00:43:08,386
but I only have two hands...

911
00:43:08,386 --> 00:43:10,088
It's such a shame.

912
00:43:10,088 --> 00:43:11,422
Thank you.

913
00:43:11,422 --> 00:43:12,824
- It was an honor.
- Thank you.

914
00:43:12,824 --> 00:43:14,325
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

915
00:43:14,325 --> 00:43:15,426
Thank you!

916
00:43:15,426 --> 00:43:17,140
- It was delicious.
- Thank you.

917
00:43:21,332 --> 00:43:23,267
[On Break]

918
00:43:23,267 --> 00:43:24,268
Okay.

919
00:43:25,870 --> 00:43:28,940
[Lunchtime]

920
00:43:28,940 --> 00:43:30,141
You put yourself out.

921
00:43:30,741 --> 00:43:33,240
Wow, this is incredible.

922
00:43:36,914 --> 00:43:38,950
It feels like a New Year's celebration.

923
00:43:38,950 --> 00:43:41,402
- Does it?
- With <i>tteokguk</i> and <i>yukjeon</i>.

924
00:43:53,231 --> 00:43:56,200
We get great benefits working here.

925
00:43:56,200 --> 00:43:58,836
- The staff benefits are unreal.
- Totally.

926
00:43:58,836 --> 00:44:00,872
[Smiling In Agreement]

927
00:44:04,208 --> 00:44:07,496
- Thank you for the food.
- Thank you for the food.

928
00:44:08,779 --> 00:44:09,780
Enjoy.

929
00:44:10,581 --> 00:44:13,885
[Furtive Glances]

930
00:44:14,385 --> 00:44:15,453
Do you need more rice cakes?

931
00:44:15,453 --> 00:44:18,222
[Why Is He Just Staring At The Food?]
Have some first.

932
00:44:20,558 --> 00:44:23,661
[Manager Hee Ae Takes A Sip]

933
00:44:25,429 --> 00:44:28,432
I'm so happy.

934
00:44:28,432 --> 00:44:30,514
The broth is so flavorful.

935
00:44:31,102 --> 00:44:35,273
[The Kitchen Team Take A Sip]

936
00:44:35,973 --> 00:44:39,110
[And Seon Ho Takes A Sip]

937
00:44:39,110 --> 00:44:43,748
[Dino Finally Picks Up His Spoon
After The Senior Staff Have Eaten First]

938
00:44:45,883 --> 00:44:48,152
- The <i>tteokguk</i>...
- It is so good.

939
00:44:48,152 --> 00:44:50,688
[Amazed]
I'm so happy.

940
00:44:50,688 --> 00:44:53,024
- The broth is so flavorful,
- It's delicious.

941
00:44:53,024 --> 00:44:54,659
like ox-bone soup.

942
00:45:04,535 --> 00:45:07,205
- Isn't it so good?
- It has a clean, simple flavor.

943
00:45:07,205 --> 00:45:08,599
[Nods In Agreement]

944
00:45:08,599 --> 00:45:11,409
Dino, this is why I come to work.

945
00:45:11,409 --> 00:45:13,778
The kimchi stew you made
on my first day here was amazing.

946
00:45:13,778 --> 00:45:16,314
- Oh, that was when you were here.
- Yes.

947
00:45:16,314 --> 00:45:18,097
It was really delicious.

948
00:45:21,018 --> 00:45:22,186
It's ox bone soup.

949
00:45:22,186 --> 00:45:24,222
[She Can't Help But Applaud]
Is it? It's really flavorful.

950
00:45:24,222 --> 00:45:26,057
- It's so tasty.
- Really?

951
00:45:28,619 --> 00:45:31,495
[A Round Of Applause]

952
00:45:31,495 --> 00:45:33,431
This is the good life.

953
00:45:33,431 --> 00:45:35,466
[That's Good To Hear]

954
00:45:35,466 --> 00:45:37,568
It's unbelievably good.

955
00:45:37,568 --> 00:45:39,170
Is it?

956
00:45:39,170 --> 00:45:41,311
This kimchi is...

957
00:45:41,906 --> 00:45:43,407
the one we received.

958
00:45:43,407 --> 00:45:46,477
- You mean from our customer?
- It goes perfectly with this <i>tteokguk</i>.

959
00:45:46,477 --> 00:45:48,937
It's the perfect pairing.

960
00:45:54,952 --> 00:45:56,187
- It's so delicious.
- What?

961
00:45:56,187 --> 00:45:58,256
- It's shockingly good.
- It's so good.

962
00:45:58,256 --> 00:46:00,091
I've never tasted <i>tteokguk</i> like this.

963
00:46:00,091 --> 00:46:01,359
- Me too.
- Right?

964
00:46:01,359 --> 00:46:03,227
- It's kind of...
- It's crazy.

965
00:46:03,227 --> 00:46:04,975
It's really delicious.

966
00:46:06,597 --> 00:46:09,867
I'm thankful that you like it.

967
00:46:09,867 --> 00:46:11,535
It must be hard enough baking.

968
00:46:11,535 --> 00:46:12,803
Thank you for going to this trouble.

969
00:46:12,803 --> 00:46:14,338
We really appreciate it.

970
00:46:14,338 --> 00:46:15,784
Try the <i>yukjeon</i>.

971
00:46:16,774 --> 00:46:18,843
- They're onions.
- You must have cooked them one by one.

972
00:46:18,843 --> 00:46:20,211
- Together?
- Eat them together.

973
00:46:20,211 --> 00:46:22,713
[Pickled Onions To Pair With <i>Yukjeon</i>]
Dip it and eat it with the onions.

974
00:46:22,713 --> 00:46:25,583
- You must have cooked them one by one.
- They're onions.

975
00:46:25,583 --> 00:46:26,851
- Together?
- Eat them together.

976
00:46:26,851 --> 00:46:28,552
- Okay.
- Dip it and eat it with the onions.

977
00:46:28,552 --> 00:46:30,762
- Dip it in this.
- Okay.

978
00:46:37,501 --> 00:46:39,964
- It tastes even better with this.
- Yes.

979
00:46:39,964 --> 00:46:43,334
[Chef Cha Even Prepared Pickled Onions ]
Try it quickly.

980
00:46:43,334 --> 00:46:44,935
Have it with the onions.

981
00:46:44,935 --> 00:46:46,570
- Really?
- Yeah.

982
00:46:47,805 --> 00:46:49,073
It's so good.

983
00:46:50,641 --> 00:46:52,036
It's amazing.

984
00:46:54,011 --> 00:46:55,846
This <i>yukjeon</i> is incredible.

985
00:46:56,580 --> 00:46:59,550
Dino came today expecting it to be quiet,

986
00:46:59,550 --> 00:47:01,419
but it's been a busy day.

987
00:47:01,419 --> 00:47:02,586
But still...

988
00:47:02,586 --> 00:47:08,025
That hat gives cafeteria worker vibes.

989
00:47:08,025 --> 00:47:09,427
How funny.

990
00:47:09,927 --> 00:47:12,596
Dino, have you tried any of the desserts?

991
00:47:12,596 --> 00:47:14,332
I tried a madeleine.

992
00:47:14,332 --> 00:47:16,008
Who said you could eat it?

993
00:47:16,734 --> 00:47:18,969
Was that meant to be a secret?

994
00:47:18,969 --> 00:47:20,974
[I Caught You Red-Handed]

995
00:47:20,974 --> 00:47:23,443
- I'm so happy.
- Me too.

996
00:47:24,083 --> 00:47:26,616
I'm really happy.

997
00:47:28,112 --> 00:47:30,247
Thank you for bringing us such joy.

998
00:47:30,247 --> 00:47:31,982
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

999
00:47:34,652 --> 00:47:36,620
- Thank you for the food.
- Thank you for the food.

1000
00:47:36,620 --> 00:47:37,688
Thank you!

1001
00:47:37,688 --> 00:47:40,224
[That Was A Great Lunch]

1002
00:47:42,360 --> 00:47:44,628
It's 3 p.m.

1003
00:47:45,062 --> 00:47:46,664
Let's go!

1004
00:47:46,664 --> 00:47:47,925
Goodness.

1005
00:47:48,666 --> 00:47:51,602
[Bonjour Bakery Is Open For The Afternoon]

1006
00:47:53,037 --> 00:47:57,241
[The First Customers Of The Afternoon]

1007
00:47:58,275 --> 00:47:59,276
- Hello.
- Welcome.

1008
00:47:59,276 --> 00:48:00,945
Come on in.

1009
00:48:00,945 --> 00:48:02,213
Welcome.

1010
00:48:03,647 --> 00:48:05,883
The flowers are so pretty.
There are so many of them.

1011
00:48:05,883 --> 00:48:08,386
- A lot of my favorite flowers are here.
- I see.

1012
00:48:08,386 --> 00:48:10,554
- Which flowers are your favorite?
- What?

1013
00:48:10,554 --> 00:48:11,789
Do you like Korean azaleas?

1014
00:48:11,789 --> 00:48:12,757
They're all lovely.

1015
00:48:12,757 --> 00:48:14,458
- Yes, they are.
- They're all pretty.

1016
00:48:14,458 --> 00:48:16,193
You should say you like
the Kim Hee Ae flower best.

1017
00:48:16,193 --> 00:48:18,963
Your son is very charming.

1018
00:48:18,963 --> 00:48:21,031
- She has appeared in many dramas.
- Yes.

1019
00:48:21,031 --> 00:48:23,300
- Thank you.
- I could tell at a glance.

1020
00:48:23,300 --> 00:48:25,269
Your earrings are gorgeous, ma'am.

1021
00:48:25,269 --> 00:48:26,470
- What?
- Your earrings.

1022
00:48:26,470 --> 00:48:28,706
My old man bought them for me.

1023
00:48:28,706 --> 00:48:30,141
- Your husband?
- Yes.

1024
00:48:30,141 --> 00:48:32,476
My husband got them for me.

1025
00:48:32,476 --> 00:48:33,711
A long time ago?

1026
00:48:33,711 --> 00:48:36,280
- He passed away about 4 or 5 years ago.
- I see.

1027
00:48:36,280 --> 00:48:37,948
- He passed away.
- I see.

1028
00:48:37,948 --> 00:48:40,985
These earrings are my only keepsake.

1029
00:48:40,985 --> 00:48:43,921
They're so precious.

1030
00:48:43,921 --> 00:48:45,856
- We'll take one of these.
- Okay.

1031
00:48:45,856 --> 00:48:47,258
[1 Kumquat Forsythia Tart]

1032
00:48:47,258 --> 00:48:50,161
- We'll have a Yuzu Madeleine.
- One Yuzu Madeleine.

1033
00:48:50,161 --> 00:48:52,072
- Just one, right?
- Yes.

1034
00:49:08,279 --> 00:49:10,548
[His Most Successful Heart]

1035
00:49:11,382 --> 00:49:14,051
This is how you should draw a heart.

1036
00:49:14,051 --> 00:49:15,119
- Not bad, right?
- It's great.

1037
00:49:15,119 --> 00:49:16,587
Okay, that's good.

1038
00:49:18,722 --> 00:49:20,791
It's okay if it fails, just give it to me.

1039
00:49:20,791 --> 00:49:22,159
Failure isn't in my dictionary.

1040
00:49:22,159 --> 00:49:23,427
- Is that so?
- Yes.

1041
00:49:23,427 --> 00:49:26,230
[Laughing]
I have no idea what you're talking about.

1042
00:49:26,230 --> 00:49:27,467
Yes.

1043
00:49:27,467 --> 00:49:31,204
I have never failed at making coffee.

1044
00:49:33,471 --> 00:49:36,240
- Courtesy of the man who never fails.
- Thank you.

1045
00:49:36,240 --> 00:49:37,608
- Here's the café latte.
- Okay.

1046
00:49:37,608 --> 00:49:39,910
- Thank you.
- Do you see that heart?

1047
00:49:39,910 --> 00:49:41,212
I drew it.

1048
00:49:41,212 --> 00:49:43,113
[Chuckling]
My goodness.

1049
00:49:43,113 --> 00:49:44,148
Thank you.

1050
00:49:44,148 --> 00:49:45,749
- Here's the description.
- You're a craftsman.

1051
00:49:45,749 --> 00:49:47,740
- I am, aren't I?
- Yes.

1052
00:49:49,186 --> 00:49:51,522
[With The Afternoon Business In Full Swing]

1053
00:49:53,357 --> 00:49:55,759
[Someone Has Slipped]

1054
00:49:55,759 --> 00:49:59,630
[From Our Minds For A Moment]

1055
00:50:02,266 --> 00:50:06,770
[It's The Person Who Reserved
The Last Remaining Cha Loaf Bread]

1056
00:50:06,770 --> 00:50:09,306
[And Now]

1057
00:50:10,808 --> 00:50:13,911
[They Are Coming To Bonjour Bakery]

1058
00:50:13,911 --> 00:50:16,380
[To Pick Up Their Order]
Would you like a Yuzu Madeleine?

1059
00:50:16,380 --> 00:50:17,414
- I see.
- All right.

1060
00:50:17,414 --> 00:50:19,550
- Welcome.
- Hello.

1061
00:50:19,550 --> 00:50:22,152
- Hello.
- Come on in.

1062
00:50:22,152 --> 00:50:23,587
[Im Jeong Ae, Pyo Ok Rye]

1063
00:50:23,587 --> 00:50:26,557
- The kimchi is delicious.
- You liked it?

1064
00:50:26,557 --> 00:50:29,627
We ate until our stomachs burst

1065
00:50:29,627 --> 00:50:31,996
- at lunch.
- I'm glad it was to your liking.

1066
00:50:31,996 --> 00:50:34,265
It was delicious.

1067
00:50:34,265 --> 00:50:35,900
You reserved a loaf of bread, right?

1068
00:50:35,900 --> 00:50:38,869
There's just one left,
and we've hidden it in the back

1069
00:50:38,869 --> 00:50:40,204
so we can give it to you.

1070
00:50:40,204 --> 00:50:41,171
- Ma'am.
- Yes?

1071
00:50:41,171 --> 00:50:42,239
Is it this?

1072
00:50:42,239 --> 00:50:43,541
[For The Neighbor Next Door]

1073
00:50:43,541 --> 00:50:45,709
[Who Always Asks For A Loaf Of Bread]
The loaf of bread will be ready tomorrow.

1074
00:50:45,709 --> 00:50:47,811
- Tomorrow?
- We just have this today.

1075
00:50:47,811 --> 00:50:48,846
It's just this today.

1076
00:50:48,846 --> 00:50:51,615
We've got one safely tucked away.

1077
00:50:51,615 --> 00:50:52,550
[Bursts Out Laughing]

1078
00:50:52,550 --> 00:50:54,919
Bring it out then.

1079
00:50:54,919 --> 00:50:57,521
[Loaf Of Bread Sales Log]
You are the owners of the very last loaf.

1080
00:50:57,521 --> 00:50:59,156
[Sold]
All right.

1081
00:50:59,156 --> 00:51:00,991
You've bought a lot of bread.

1082
00:51:00,991 --> 00:51:02,393
She really has.

1083
00:51:02,393 --> 00:51:04,831
I plan to live on bread.

1084
00:51:04,831 --> 00:51:06,497
I'm so touched.

1085
00:51:10,434 --> 00:51:13,337
Okay, I'll ring up two.

1086
00:51:13,337 --> 00:51:15,172
Look over here.

1087
00:51:15,172 --> 00:51:17,308
Let me shake your hand.

1088
00:51:17,308 --> 00:51:18,976
- How have you been?
- I'm good.

1089
00:51:18,976 --> 00:51:21,545
- Do you know who I am?
- Of course.

1090
00:51:21,545 --> 00:51:23,514
I recognized you at once.

1091
00:51:23,514 --> 00:51:25,049
We were always together
when we were younger,

1092
00:51:25,049 --> 00:51:26,550
- so how could I not know you?
- Right.

1093
00:51:26,550 --> 00:51:27,551
We were always...

1094
00:51:27,551 --> 00:51:29,320
- I also know her.
- Of course.

1095
00:51:29,320 --> 00:51:30,254
I know everyone.

1096
00:51:30,254 --> 00:51:32,823
- You're all in great shape.
- Yes, we're doing well.

1097
00:51:32,823 --> 00:51:34,325
We used to meet up every day.

1098
00:51:34,325 --> 00:51:35,759
- We met every morning.
- We did.

1099
00:51:35,759 --> 00:51:38,562
I didn't recognize you
because we're older now.

1100
00:51:38,562 --> 00:51:40,698
Right? We've gotten older.

1101
00:51:40,698 --> 00:51:41,732
You've gotten even prettier.

1102
00:51:41,732 --> 00:51:43,601
How many siblings do you have?

1103
00:51:43,601 --> 00:51:45,269
I have four siblings.

1104
00:51:45,269 --> 00:51:46,837
How is Hoe Ryong and everyone?

1105
00:51:46,837 --> 00:51:48,606
They passed away a long time ago.

1106
00:51:48,606 --> 00:51:50,074
- It's been almost a decade.
- What?

1107
00:51:50,074 --> 00:51:53,210
- They passed away ten years ago.
- Really?

1108
00:51:53,210 --> 00:51:55,312
But they were so healthy.

1109
00:51:55,312 --> 00:51:56,447
What about Dae Cheon?

1110
00:51:56,447 --> 00:51:58,682
- They passed away about...
- How long ago?

1111
00:51:58,682 --> 00:52:00,451
- It's been over 5 years, maybe 10 years.
- Ma'am.

1112
00:52:00,451 --> 00:52:02,539
- Ten years?
- Here's your loaf of bread.

1113
00:52:08,926 --> 00:52:11,195
- Enjoy your dessert.
- Sure.

1114
00:52:11,929 --> 00:52:13,230
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1115
00:52:13,230 --> 00:52:14,798
Bye.

1116
00:52:14,798 --> 00:52:16,233
Ma'am.

1117
00:52:16,233 --> 00:52:17,659
Get home safely.

1118
00:52:18,535 --> 00:52:20,104
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1119
00:52:20,104 --> 00:52:21,772
Thank you for coming.

1120
00:52:21,772 --> 00:52:23,240
Did you ask if I'm cold?

1121
00:52:23,240 --> 00:52:24,475
I said thank you for coming.

1122
00:52:24,475 --> 00:52:26,143
- Yes.
- Thank you.

1123
00:52:26,143 --> 00:52:28,045
- Thanks for the bread.
- We're the ones who are thankful.

1124
00:52:28,045 --> 00:52:31,181
- I don't know when I'll see you again.
- I know.

1125
00:52:31,181 --> 00:52:32,783
When will we ever meet again?

1126
00:52:32,783 --> 00:52:34,551
Since today is our last day...

1127
00:52:35,819 --> 00:52:38,488
- Take care of yourself.
- You too, ma'am.

1128
00:52:41,291 --> 00:52:44,194
We won't be seeing them tomorrow.

1129
00:52:44,194 --> 00:52:47,756
- It's making me terribly sad.
- Yeah.

1130
00:52:51,402 --> 00:52:52,936
Someone else is coming.

1131
00:52:54,972 --> 00:52:56,707
It looks like they've had a drink.

1132
00:52:58,342 --> 00:52:59,643
You can tell from here?

1133
00:52:59,643 --> 00:53:00,778
Yes.

1134
00:53:00,778 --> 00:53:01,945
They're a regular.

1135
00:53:01,945 --> 00:53:03,547
Oh, I see.

1136
00:53:04,348 --> 00:53:06,316
- Hello.
- Seon Ho!

1137
00:53:06,316 --> 00:53:07,618
Hello!

1138
00:53:08,886 --> 00:53:11,188
It seems like you've had a drink.

1139
00:53:11,188 --> 00:53:13,257
How did you know that?

1140
00:53:13,257 --> 00:53:14,324
Can you smell it?

1141
00:53:14,324 --> 00:53:16,026
I can tell just by your face
since you're a regular.

1142
00:53:16,026 --> 00:53:17,795
I can tell by the color of your face.

1143
00:53:17,795 --> 00:53:19,763
- I had a drink.
- Did you?

1144
00:53:19,763 --> 00:53:22,132
What will we do? This is so sad.

1145
00:53:22,132 --> 00:53:23,611
- I know.
- I heard today's your last day.

1146
00:53:23,611 --> 00:53:26,403
Yes, it's our final day.

1147
00:53:26,403 --> 00:53:28,205
It's our last time meeting like this.

1148
00:53:28,205 --> 00:53:29,373
[It's Such A Shame]

1149
00:53:29,373 --> 00:53:31,208
This wasn't on the menu yesterday.

1150
00:53:31,208 --> 00:53:32,342
- It wasn't?
- No.

1151
00:53:32,342 --> 00:53:34,144
- Give us one of these.
- Okay.

1152
00:53:34,144 --> 00:53:36,046
- The camellia one is new as well.
- We'll take this one.

1153
00:53:36,046 --> 00:53:37,314
- The Camellia Tart?
- Yes.

1154
00:53:37,314 --> 00:53:39,483
- That's enough.
- We've tried everything now.

1155
00:53:39,483 --> 00:53:41,257
You've tried it all?

1156
00:53:41,257 --> 00:53:43,420
- I've been here every day.
- I know.

1157
00:53:43,420 --> 00:53:46,223
You came even though you've been drinking.

1158
00:53:46,223 --> 00:53:48,492
I wasn't going to come today,
but I came anyway.

1159
00:53:50,461 --> 00:53:51,762
[Bonjour Bakery]

1160
00:53:51,762 --> 00:53:54,064
[Current Time 4 p.m.]

1161
00:53:54,064 --> 00:53:55,532
- Hello.
- Hello.

1162
00:53:55,532 --> 00:53:57,267
- Welcome.
- Welcome.

1163
00:53:57,267 --> 00:53:58,335
Hello.

1164
00:53:58,335 --> 00:54:00,138
Hi, welcome.

1165
00:54:00,971 --> 00:54:04,201
You really look like an actor.
Your face is so delicate.

1166
00:54:04,201 --> 00:54:06,043
- You're so gorgeous.
- Oh, please.

1167
00:54:06,043 --> 00:54:07,411
You're so beautiful.

1168
00:54:07,411 --> 00:54:09,413
Thank you.

1169
00:54:09,413 --> 00:54:11,215
You're so handsome.

1170
00:54:11,215 --> 00:54:13,150
[A Deep Bow Of Thanks]
Thank you.

1171
00:54:14,618 --> 00:54:16,353
What would you like, sir?

1172
00:54:16,353 --> 00:54:18,722
[Close-Knit Colleagues
Enjoying Time Together After Work]

1173
00:54:18,722 --> 00:54:21,859
One Green Barley Field Tart
and one Forsythia Tart.

1174
00:54:21,859 --> 00:54:23,994
- Can you plate them?
- Which table?

1175
00:54:23,994 --> 00:54:25,785
- Table Four.
- Okay.

1176
00:54:27,865 --> 00:54:30,134
[While Seon Ho Puts In The Order]

1177
00:54:30,768 --> 00:54:33,504
[Manager Hee Ae Makes The Honey Lemon Tea]

1178
00:54:34,471 --> 00:54:37,407
[And Part-Timer Chan Plates The Desserts]

1179
00:54:38,108 --> 00:54:41,745
[A Bond Tighter Than Dough]

1180
00:54:41,745 --> 00:54:43,129
Excuse me.

1181
00:54:43,129 --> 00:54:44,681
They've got it under control.

1182
00:54:44,681 --> 00:54:47,351
[3 Orangeades, 1 Bonjour <i>Bokbunja</i> Croissant]

1183
00:54:47,351 --> 00:54:49,787
[1 Bonjour Green Barley Field Tart
1 Bonjour Kumquat Forsythia Tart]

1184
00:54:49,787 --> 00:54:51,488
They're so pretty.

1185
00:54:51,488 --> 00:54:52,756
Who made these?

1186
00:54:52,756 --> 00:54:54,191
Chef Cha Seung Won made them.

1187
00:54:54,191 --> 00:54:55,395
[All Desserts Are Made By Chef Cha]

1188
00:54:55,395 --> 00:54:57,004
They're so pretty.

1189
00:54:57,004 --> 00:54:58,098
- Thank you.
- Sure.

1190
00:54:58,098 --> 00:54:59,299
Enjoy.

1191
00:55:01,999 --> 00:55:05,302
It's not great lighting for a photo.

1192
00:55:05,302 --> 00:55:08,138
Eat up.

1193
00:55:08,138 --> 00:55:11,375
You're surrounded
by such talented employees

1194
00:55:11,375 --> 00:55:14,812
who seem to really respect you.

1195
00:55:14,812 --> 00:55:16,547
- He's such a good person.
- I see that.

1196
00:55:16,547 --> 00:55:19,514
We all grew up in Iksan.

1197
00:55:20,551 --> 00:55:22,152
- Your hometown is Iksan?
- Yes.

1198
00:55:22,152 --> 00:55:23,587
- I'm from Iksan.
- Really?

1199
00:55:23,587 --> 00:55:24,922
Yes.

1200
00:55:24,922 --> 00:55:28,125
There's that person in Iksan who...

1201
00:55:28,125 --> 00:55:32,029
There's someone who runs a dance studio,
and their son's an idol.

1202
00:55:32,029 --> 00:55:33,130
I'm that son.

1203
00:55:33,130 --> 00:55:34,898
- I thought so!
- The dance studio.

1204
00:55:34,898 --> 00:55:35,933
I'm that son.

1205
00:55:35,933 --> 00:55:37,534
- I thought so!
- The dance studio.

1206
00:55:37,534 --> 00:55:40,103
- What a crazy coincidence.
- The dance studio in Yeongdeung.

1207
00:55:40,103 --> 00:55:42,339
- It's on the second or third floor.
- That's right.

1208
00:55:42,339 --> 00:55:43,307
Did you take lessons there?

1209
00:55:43,307 --> 00:55:45,242
- I didn't take lessons myself,
- I heard about it.

1210
00:55:45,242 --> 00:55:46,543
But I heard about it.

1211
00:55:46,543 --> 00:55:49,680
I heard the owner's son
is a successful idol.

1212
00:55:49,680 --> 00:55:51,215
Yes, that's me.

1213
00:55:51,215 --> 00:55:54,952
- He was just performing abroad,
- This is so sudden.

1214
00:55:54,952 --> 00:55:58,322
And he came here to help
as soon as he got back to the country.

1215
00:55:58,322 --> 00:56:00,250
What are the odds?

1216
00:56:00,250 --> 00:56:03,794
That's impressive.
The pride of Iksan.

1217
00:56:03,794 --> 00:56:06,230
- Thank you.
- It's nice to meet you.

1218
00:56:06,230 --> 00:56:08,398
No wonder your face is so radiant.

1219
00:56:09,433 --> 00:56:11,501
- Thank you.
- The pride of Iksan.

1220
00:56:12,353 --> 00:56:13,704
Are you holding up okay?

1221
00:56:13,704 --> 00:56:14,805
Yes.

1222
00:56:14,805 --> 00:56:17,908
- It's the perfect level of busy.
- Right?

1223
00:56:17,908 --> 00:56:19,076
People who are good at one thing

1224
00:56:19,076 --> 00:56:21,357
- tend to be good at everything else.
- I really think so.

1225
00:56:22,212 --> 00:56:24,715
- It applies to you as well.
- I still have a long way to go.

1226
00:56:26,884 --> 00:56:30,554
How strange. It's time to close up but...

1227
00:56:31,521 --> 00:56:35,025
[Hoping At Least One More Customer
Will Come Before Closing]

1228
00:56:37,160 --> 00:56:38,996
Are you closed now?

1229
00:56:38,996 --> 00:56:41,164
- No, we close at 6 p.m.
- Is that right?

1230
00:56:41,164 --> 00:56:43,367
Yes, what brings you by?

1231
00:56:43,367 --> 00:56:46,603
I live right here.
I'm just getting back from a trip.

1232
00:56:46,603 --> 00:56:48,872
- Where did you go?
- I was at the village hall.

1233
00:56:48,872 --> 00:56:50,040
Good.

1234
00:56:50,040 --> 00:56:52,709
You need to move about
as much as possible.

1235
00:56:52,709 --> 00:56:54,578
What's there to do at home?

1236
00:56:54,578 --> 00:56:56,179
You need to get some fresh air,
meet people,

1237
00:56:56,179 --> 00:56:59,349
spend time outdoors
so you don't feel cooped up.

1238
00:56:59,349 --> 00:57:01,051
Are you heading home to make dinner?

1239
00:57:01,051 --> 00:57:03,799
I'm going to the gym to exercise.

1240
00:57:04,391 --> 00:57:06,496
Good on you.

1241
00:57:07,491 --> 00:57:09,326
- Have a nice time.
- Take care.

1242
00:57:09,326 --> 00:57:10,584
All right.

1243
00:57:15,165 --> 00:57:20,737
[Another Party Has Arrived
As Manager Hee Ae Hoped]

1244
00:57:22,039 --> 00:57:23,173
Hello.

1245
00:57:23,173 --> 00:57:24,508
- Welcome.
- Welcome.

1246
00:57:24,508 --> 00:57:26,543
Over here. Two people, right?

1247
00:57:26,543 --> 00:57:28,596
- Yes.
- You can take a seat.

1248
00:57:29,780 --> 00:57:31,448
- Hello.
- Hello.

1249
00:57:31,448 --> 00:57:33,317
- We serve bread...
- Thank you for serving us.

1250
00:57:33,317 --> 00:57:34,484
Thank you for coming.

1251
00:57:34,484 --> 00:57:36,153
Look how handsome you are.

1252
00:57:36,153 --> 00:57:37,321
You're Seon Ho.

1253
00:57:37,321 --> 00:57:38,755
Yes, that's right.

1254
00:57:38,755 --> 00:57:40,023
You're on TV a lot.

1255
00:57:40,023 --> 00:57:41,992
I appear every so often.

1256
00:57:41,992 --> 00:57:43,523
- I know.
- Yes.

1257
00:57:46,897 --> 00:57:48,565
Excuse me.

1258
00:57:49,700 --> 00:57:51,101
All right.

1259
00:57:51,101 --> 00:57:53,270
Here's your Americano.

1260
00:57:55,272 --> 00:57:56,473
Can we take a picture?

1261
00:57:56,473 --> 00:57:58,056
Of course.

1262
00:57:59,242 --> 00:58:01,878
My kids begged me to take a photo.

1263
00:58:01,878 --> 00:58:03,914
[How Cute]

1264
00:58:03,914 --> 00:58:05,716
Try a bite.

1265
00:58:05,716 --> 00:58:07,087
[Click]

1266
00:58:07,087 --> 00:58:09,553
How is the coffee?

1267
00:58:09,553 --> 00:58:11,728
It's good.

1268
00:58:15,058 --> 00:58:16,361
I made it.

1269
00:58:17,594 --> 00:58:19,596
- See you again.
- Take care.

1270
00:58:19,596 --> 00:58:20,860
- Bye.
- Bye.

1271
00:58:23,300 --> 00:58:25,235
What time is it?

1272
00:58:25,235 --> 00:58:29,373
[5 p.m. Closing Time]

1273
00:58:29,373 --> 00:58:33,110
[The Staff Sit Down Together After Closing]

1274
00:58:33,643 --> 00:58:35,112
Do you know what that bread is called?

1275
00:58:35,112 --> 00:58:37,948
[A Surprise Planned By Chef Cha]
It's called a galette des rois.

1276
00:58:37,948 --> 00:58:40,684
[Bonjour Sweet Potato Galette Des Rois]

1277
00:58:41,485 --> 00:58:44,621
[The Pie Of Kings]

1278
00:58:48,091 --> 00:58:50,627
<i>In France, every New Year,</i>

1279
00:58:50,627 --> 00:58:53,764
[A Bread Of Good Luck Shared With Family]
<i>families gather and eat it together.</i>

1280
00:58:53,764 --> 00:58:55,465
<i>They put a porcelain figurine in it.</i>

1281
00:58:55,465 --> 00:58:56,800
[The Figurine Is Called A Fève]

1282
00:58:56,800 --> 00:59:00,804
[They Put A Lucky Charm Inside The Galette]

1283
00:59:00,804 --> 00:59:04,207
<i>They each get a slice,
and whoever gets the figurine is the king.</i>

1284
00:59:04,207 --> 00:59:05,709
[The King Of The Day
Is Wished A Year Of Good Fortune]

1285
00:59:05,709 --> 00:59:09,413
In the same spirit,
since we can't use a figurine,

1286
00:59:09,413 --> 00:59:11,114
we'll put a chestnut
inside the pie instead.

1287
00:59:11,114 --> 00:59:12,783
[A Single Bite-Sized Candied Chestnut]

1288
00:59:12,783 --> 00:59:16,953
[We Plan To Pack A Little Luck
Into This Chestnut]

1289
00:59:16,953 --> 00:59:19,022
Am I supposed to eat bread every day?

1290
00:59:19,022 --> 00:59:22,526
[And Share It With Everyone
Who Became Part Of The Bonjour Bakery]

1291
00:59:22,526 --> 00:59:23,960
One, two...

1292
00:59:23,960 --> 00:59:24,960
Oh, we're doing this.

1293
00:59:25,762 --> 00:59:28,065
- That's so cute!
- This is...

1294
00:59:28,065 --> 00:59:31,601
Why don't we wrap things up like that?

1295
00:59:31,601 --> 00:59:33,537
- It's a great idea. They'll love it.
- It's meaningful.

1296
00:59:33,537 --> 00:59:39,276
Also, the reason we made this program

1297
00:59:39,276 --> 00:59:42,612
is for seniors who have never
experienced anything like this before.

1298
00:59:42,612 --> 00:59:44,414
- That's why we did it.
- Yes.

1299
00:59:44,414 --> 00:59:46,943
I think it's very meaningful in that way.

1300
00:59:51,855 --> 00:59:54,958
[Five Portions Of Fluffy
Sweet Potato Filling]

1301
00:59:55,559 --> 00:59:57,060
[One Of Those]

1302
00:59:57,060 --> 01:00:00,997
[Is Filled With The Small Lucky Chestnut]

1303
01:00:03,934 --> 01:00:08,071
[Cut The Dough To Wrap
Around The Sweet Potato Filling]

1304
01:00:10,140 --> 01:00:12,375
[Take Out The Frozen Sweet Potato Filling]

1305
01:00:12,375 --> 01:00:16,413
[And Put It Inside The Dough]

1306
01:00:24,621 --> 01:00:27,090
[Place The Dough Over The Filling]

1307
01:00:27,090 --> 01:00:30,427
[And Firmly Seal The Edges]

1308
01:00:35,132 --> 01:00:39,002
[Place A 12cm Ring On Top
And Trim The Edges Off]

1309
01:00:46,209 --> 01:00:49,446
[The King Of Baking Waves His Knife
Gracefully In The Air]

1310
01:00:53,917 --> 01:00:55,318
Galette!

1311
01:00:55,318 --> 01:00:59,256
[The King Of Baking's Final Mission]

1312
01:01:00,357 --> 01:01:03,260
[A Flower Atop A Galette]

1313
01:01:04,327 --> 01:01:08,064
[This Beautiful Pattern Of Delicate Lines]

1314
01:01:08,064 --> 01:01:09,032
It should go straight down.

1315
01:01:09,032 --> 01:01:11,268
[Must Be Drawn One Line At A Time]
That's one...

1316
01:01:11,268 --> 01:01:13,105
Just until that point.

1317
01:01:16,239 --> 01:01:18,308
[A Pinnacle Of Beauty]

1318
01:01:18,308 --> 01:01:21,878
[That Befits A King Of Baking]

1319
01:01:27,184 --> 01:01:29,719
[The Center Is Marked With A Cross]

1320
01:01:32,756 --> 01:01:34,558
[And Curved Lines Are Drawn]

1321
01:01:34,558 --> 01:01:39,095
[With A Graceful Sweeping Motion]

1322
01:01:51,408 --> 01:01:54,544
[A Masterpiece Shaped By The Tip Of A Knife]

1323
01:02:13,600 --> 01:02:18,404
[A Golden Brown Finish
Crafted Through Time And Care]

1324
01:02:29,246 --> 01:02:31,381
[Who Will Take Home The Piece Of Luck]

1325
01:02:31,381 --> 01:02:34,317
[Tucked Inside This Glossy Golden Pie?]

1326
01:02:34,985 --> 01:02:39,589
[Bonjour Sweet Potato Galette De Rois!]

1327
01:02:40,523 --> 01:02:46,229
[Bonjour Bakery Current Time 5:20 p.m.]

1328
01:02:46,229 --> 01:02:51,167
[10 Minutes Before The Event]

1329
01:02:51,568 --> 01:02:53,303
It's nice living in this neighborhood.

1330
01:02:53,303 --> 01:02:55,823
[It Feels Good To Be Out Often]
I keep getting invited to places.

1331
01:03:00,443 --> 01:03:03,013
[I'm So Tired]

1332
01:03:03,013 --> 01:03:05,370
That must be quite a hassle.

1333
01:03:06,416 --> 01:03:09,807
You should get a membership.

1334
01:03:10,587 --> 01:03:12,756
Hello, you're here.

1335
01:03:12,756 --> 01:03:14,557
We heard there's a party.

1336
01:03:14,557 --> 01:03:16,593
- That's right.
- Party.

1337
01:03:17,327 --> 01:03:19,296
[What Is That Rumbling Noise]

1338
01:03:19,296 --> 01:03:21,631
[That Is Getting Closer To The Party Venue?]

1339
01:03:23,833 --> 01:03:26,369
[Did You Order A Helicopter For The Party?]

1340
01:03:28,305 --> 01:03:30,407
[That's Not It]

1341
01:03:30,407 --> 01:03:34,210
[It's A Tractor,
Done With Work And Ready To Party]

1342
01:03:40,984 --> 01:03:42,290
Hello!

1343
01:03:43,820 --> 01:03:45,233
Park there.

1344
01:03:46,690 --> 01:03:48,358
My gosh.

1345
01:03:48,758 --> 01:03:51,185
[We'd Better Hurry]
That is the real deal.

1346
01:03:52,062 --> 01:03:54,698
[Let's Load Up The Tables For The Feast]

1347
01:04:00,704 --> 01:04:02,772
Ki Taek, serve the coffee.

1348
01:04:02,772 --> 01:04:03,840
If you say so.

1349
01:04:04,507 --> 01:04:06,976
Is that how you talk to your boss?

1350
01:04:06,976 --> 01:04:08,378
No.

1351
01:04:08,378 --> 01:04:09,717
It's not?

1352
01:04:10,714 --> 01:04:12,382
Should we invite them in now?

1353
01:04:12,382 --> 01:04:13,683
Yes.

1354
01:04:13,683 --> 01:04:15,051
[5:30 p.m. Time To Welcome Our Honored Guests]

1355
01:04:15,051 --> 01:04:16,519
The party is starting!

1356
01:04:16,519 --> 01:04:17,854
- Come on in.
- How exciting is this?

1357
01:04:17,854 --> 01:04:19,730
- Yes, come in.
- Hello.

1358
01:04:20,957 --> 01:04:22,492
[A Party For The Seniors]

1359
01:04:22,492 --> 01:04:24,561
- Should we park this here?
- Yes.

1360
01:04:24,561 --> 01:04:26,830
[Who Have Regularly Frequented Our Bakery]
All right.

1361
01:04:26,830 --> 01:04:28,109
Hello.

1362
01:04:30,233 --> 01:04:33,303
[A Celebration of Gratitude]
Sit anywhere you like.

1363
01:04:33,303 --> 01:04:35,372
You can sit here if you want.

1364
01:04:35,372 --> 01:04:37,374
- You first, Mom.
- Hello.

1365
01:04:39,542 --> 01:04:40,883
This way...

1366
01:04:42,011 --> 01:04:44,013
Where? Over there?

1367
01:04:45,181 --> 01:04:46,622
You're back.

1368
01:04:50,954 --> 01:04:51,888
Here.

1369
01:04:51,888 --> 01:04:53,590
You give it to him.

1370
01:04:53,590 --> 01:04:55,158
Give it to Seon Ho.

1371
01:04:55,925 --> 01:04:57,060
Thank you.

1372
01:04:57,060 --> 01:04:58,061
- Lucky you.
- This is lit.

1373
01:04:58,061 --> 01:04:59,796
It's lit!

1374
01:04:59,796 --> 01:05:01,030
- Lucky you!
- This is lit!

1375
01:05:01,030 --> 01:05:02,198
How do you know that slang?

1376
01:05:02,198 --> 01:05:03,867
She's familiar with slang.

1377
01:05:03,867 --> 01:05:05,935
[<i>Bokbunja</i> Wine]
I made that myself.

1378
01:05:05,935 --> 01:05:08,425
It's not your average market wine.

1379
01:05:11,474 --> 01:05:13,209
Try this as well.

1380
01:05:13,209 --> 01:05:14,978
- We'll enjoy it.
- Please do.

1381
01:05:14,978 --> 01:05:16,618
[Making Sure All The Guests Are Satisfied]

1382
01:05:17,147 --> 01:05:18,715
I'll cut that for you.

1383
01:05:18,715 --> 01:05:22,685
[A Celebration Shared With Grateful Hearts]

1384
01:05:23,553 --> 01:05:25,836
Are you out of tea?
I'll bring you some more.

1385
01:05:26,523 --> 01:05:28,017
But first, here you go.

1386
01:05:28,892 --> 01:05:31,694
[Out Of The Blue,
Hee Ae Collects Some Hot Water]

1387
01:05:31,694 --> 01:05:35,498
[And Heads Over Somewhere
With Chamomile Tea]

1388
01:05:36,766 --> 01:05:39,269
[It's For The Owner Who Might Be Thirsty]
Ma'am, drink this tea.

1389
01:05:39,269 --> 01:05:40,537
Thank you.

1390
01:05:40,537 --> 01:05:42,539
Let it steep a bit first.

1391
01:05:42,539 --> 01:05:43,886
She's right.

1392
01:05:44,707 --> 01:05:46,309
There's not much to life.

1393
01:05:46,309 --> 01:05:48,611
The only thing missing is a shot of soju.

1394
01:05:48,611 --> 01:05:50,246
Just zip it.

1395
01:05:50,246 --> 01:05:52,782
- Don't talk nonsense.
- What did he say?

1396
01:05:52,782 --> 01:05:55,084
He wants to have some soju.

1397
01:05:55,084 --> 01:05:56,019
[Enjoying The Show]

1398
01:05:56,019 --> 01:05:58,755
[While His Wife Scolds His Friend]
Don't talk nonsense.

1399
01:05:58,755 --> 01:06:02,025
[He Dips His Tart Into His Coffee]
He wants to have some soju.

1400
01:06:02,425 --> 01:06:06,095
[Enjoying The French Dessert In His Own Way]

1401
01:06:06,095 --> 01:06:08,064
Don't eat this just yet.

1402
01:06:08,064 --> 01:06:09,766
- Okay.
- Hold on.

1403
01:06:09,766 --> 01:06:11,405
Just wait.

1404
01:06:11,935 --> 01:06:13,670
- This bread is for you.
- Okay.

1405
01:06:13,670 --> 01:06:17,240
But don't eat it yet. Wait just a moment.

1406
01:06:17,240 --> 01:06:19,542
- Wait until the party?
- Yes, we prepared a special event.

1407
01:06:19,542 --> 01:06:20,643
- All right.
- Okay.

1408
01:06:20,643 --> 01:06:22,912
Don't eat this just yet.

1409
01:06:22,912 --> 01:06:24,745
I'll explain in a bit.

1410
01:06:25,982 --> 01:06:27,650
Here you go, ma'am. Don't eat it just yet.

1411
01:06:27,650 --> 01:06:29,786
- Okay?
- All right, I won't.

1412
01:06:29,786 --> 01:06:32,655
- Don't eat it yet.
- Okay.

1413
01:06:32,655 --> 01:06:34,824
I'm sorry to interrupt.

1414
01:06:34,824 --> 01:06:36,893
Sorry, can I have
your attention for a second?

1415
01:06:36,893 --> 01:06:40,063
[I'm Listening]
Sir. Ma'am. Can I have your attention?

1416
01:06:40,063 --> 01:06:43,733
You know the bread I just gave you?
The one with the crown.

1417
01:06:43,733 --> 01:06:47,237
It's called a galette des rois,
and they eat it in France every January,

1418
01:06:47,237 --> 01:06:50,640
just like we eat <i>tteokguk</i>
on New Year's Day.

1419
01:06:50,640 --> 01:06:52,375
A porcelain figure

1420
01:06:52,375 --> 01:06:55,011
is often placed inside the bread.

1421
01:06:55,011 --> 01:06:57,247
But since we couldn't do that,

1422
01:06:57,247 --> 01:06:59,115
we put a chestnut inside instead.

1423
01:06:59,115 --> 01:07:02,151
We put a chestnut in one of the five...

1424
01:07:02,151 --> 01:07:04,420
Sir. Ma'am. Don't eat it yet.

1425
01:07:04,420 --> 01:07:06,723
When I count to three... Wait a minute.

1426
01:07:06,723 --> 01:07:09,225
Ma'am. Sir, stop. Hold on.

1427
01:07:10,693 --> 01:07:12,762
Don't eat it now. Just wait a bit.

1428
01:07:12,762 --> 01:07:15,331
When I count to three,

1429
01:07:15,331 --> 01:07:16,232
[Pouting Slightly]

1430
01:07:16,232 --> 01:07:18,801
cut the bread with your knife.

1431
01:07:18,801 --> 01:07:21,304
All right. One.

1432
01:07:21,304 --> 01:07:22,642
Two.

1433
01:07:23,506 --> 01:07:25,001
Three! Go on.

1434
01:07:27,143 --> 01:07:28,411
All right.

1435
01:07:31,848 --> 01:07:33,783
- Should we cut it?
- Yes, try cutting it.

1436
01:07:33,783 --> 01:07:35,618
- The chestnut is about this size.
- Okay.

1437
01:07:35,618 --> 01:07:38,288
If you find a chestnut...

1438
01:07:39,322 --> 01:07:41,291
Is there no chestnut?

1439
01:07:41,291 --> 01:07:42,638
We don't have one.

1440
01:07:43,159 --> 01:07:44,427
I got one!

1441
01:07:44,427 --> 01:07:45,795
You got a chestnut?

1442
01:07:48,531 --> 01:07:49,699
I got one!

1443
01:07:49,699 --> 01:07:51,911
- You got a chestnut?
- Oh, my.

1444
01:07:53,570 --> 01:07:56,039
[They Found A Chestnut]

1445
01:07:56,039 --> 01:07:57,307
All right, then.

1446
01:07:57,307 --> 01:07:59,909
- This flower is a gift for you.
- Thank you.

1447
01:07:59,909 --> 01:08:03,112
- Let me crown you.
- All right.

1448
01:08:03,947 --> 01:08:06,316
[He Hasn't Given Up]
Cut it with the knife like this.

1449
01:08:06,316 --> 01:08:08,418
Don't you have a knife?

1450
01:08:08,418 --> 01:08:10,119
There are no more chestnuts, sir.

1451
01:08:10,119 --> 01:08:11,888
There was only one,

1452
01:08:11,888 --> 01:08:13,823
- so you can stop cutting.
- Okay.

1453
01:08:13,823 --> 01:08:15,224
[Let's Try The Sweet Potato Galette]

1454
01:08:15,224 --> 01:08:16,526
Yeah, there are no more chestnuts.

1455
01:08:16,526 --> 01:08:18,761
Ma'am. Sir. This is a gift for you.

1456
01:08:18,761 --> 01:08:21,764
- It's a gesture of our gratitude.
- You look so lovely, ma'am.

1457
01:08:21,764 --> 01:08:24,167
Thank you so much.

1458
01:08:24,167 --> 01:08:27,837
We've really enjoyed our time in Gochang.

1459
01:08:27,837 --> 01:08:29,472
Thank you for everything.

1460
01:08:29,472 --> 01:08:33,109
We've really enjoyed our time in Gochang.

1461
01:08:33,109 --> 01:08:34,944
[After Saying Goodbye]
Thank you for everything.

1462
01:08:34,944 --> 01:08:36,613
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1463
01:08:36,613 --> 01:08:37,947
Thank you for everything.

1464
01:08:37,947 --> 01:08:41,618
[It Suddenly Hit Home
That This Is The Last Day]

1465
01:08:46,322 --> 01:08:48,958
[Seeing Her Smile Like A Young Girl]

1466
01:08:48,958 --> 01:08:52,695
[Over A Small Gift]

1467
01:08:53,096 --> 01:08:57,100
[Moved Us In A Way
That Is Hard To Put Into Words]

1468
01:08:58,267 --> 01:09:00,336
Oh, man.

1469
01:09:00,336 --> 01:09:02,338
I'm in a weird mood, Dino.

1470
01:09:02,338 --> 01:09:04,974
- I can imagine.
- Yeah.

1471
01:09:10,179 --> 01:09:12,582
Who got the chestnut?

1472
01:09:13,182 --> 01:09:16,019
Whoever got the chestnut
should sing a song!

1473
01:09:18,287 --> 01:09:21,024
I'll sing for you if you want.
Just tell me the title.

1474
01:09:21,024 --> 01:09:23,793
I'll do it since I got the chestnut.

1475
01:09:26,562 --> 01:09:28,898
Here is your microphone, ma'am.

1476
01:09:28,898 --> 01:09:31,134
Here's your microphone.

1477
01:09:36,305 --> 01:09:41,044
<i>♪ Even when the pain is unbearable. ♪</i>

1478
01:09:41,044 --> 01:09:42,412
<i>[A Woman's Life</i> By Lee Mi Ja]

1479
01:09:42,412 --> 01:09:46,616
<i>- ♪ Even when my heart breaks. ♪
- ♪ Heart breaks. ♪</i>

1480
01:09:46,616 --> 01:09:48,365
- You're doing great!
- You're doing great!

1481
01:09:49,152 --> 01:09:54,194
<i>♪ Because I was born a woman. ♪</i>

1482
01:09:54,924 --> 01:10:00,930
<i>♪ I just have to bear it. ♪</i>

1483
01:10:01,635 --> 01:10:05,172
<i>♪ I have to bear the unimaginable sorrow. ♪</i>

1484
01:10:05,172 --> 01:10:09,243
<i>♪ All on my own. ♪</i>

1485
01:10:09,243 --> 01:10:13,676
<i>♪ As I stumble through. ♪</i>

1486
01:10:13,676 --> 01:10:17,246
<i>♪ This hard journey of life. ♪</i>

1487
01:10:17,246 --> 01:10:20,917
<i>♪ I have to bear it. ♪</i>

1488
01:10:21,517 --> 01:10:24,415
<i>♪ As they say... ♪</i>

1489
01:10:30,626 --> 01:10:34,731
I moved here after getting married at 23.

1490
01:10:34,731 --> 01:10:37,734
Back then, we moved in by wagon.

1491
01:10:38,501 --> 01:10:40,103
[She Arrived In An Ox Wagon To Get Married]
Here it is.

1492
01:10:40,103 --> 01:10:42,505
[Still In The Bloom Of Her Youth And Beauty]
You look so beautiful.

1493
01:10:42,505 --> 01:10:45,232
- You were stunning.
- I looked pretty back then.

1494
01:10:46,309 --> 01:10:49,479
You're still pretty,
but you were such a beautiful bride.

1495
01:10:49,479 --> 01:10:51,881
I've had a really tough life.

1496
01:10:51,881 --> 01:10:54,484
There were several times I almost died,

1497
01:10:54,484 --> 01:10:56,804
and my husband saved me.

1498
01:10:57,620 --> 01:11:00,423
I was riding a four-wheeled motorbike

1499
01:11:00,423 --> 01:11:02,925
down a hill one day

1500
01:11:02,925 --> 01:11:05,561
and ended up falling into a field.

1501
01:11:12,001 --> 01:11:16,506
I can't really think clearly
because I've been in a lot of accidents.

1502
01:11:16,506 --> 01:11:19,776
I'm just so thankful
because he's so good to me.

1503
01:11:19,776 --> 01:11:21,944
Oh, please. I don't do much.

1504
01:11:21,944 --> 01:11:25,581
Everyone said I wasn't going to make it,

1505
01:11:25,581 --> 01:11:28,618
but he called an ambulance and saved me.

1506
01:11:29,318 --> 01:11:30,987
Since marrying me,

1507
01:11:30,987 --> 01:11:34,518
she's just gone through a lot of trouble.

1508
01:11:36,459 --> 01:11:40,730
She's had a rough life,

1509
01:11:40,730 --> 01:11:44,300
and I don't know
how much time we have left,

1510
01:11:44,300 --> 01:11:45,935
but while we're still alive,

1511
01:11:45,935 --> 01:11:47,904
we should make each other happy.

1512
01:11:47,904 --> 01:11:49,518
- That's right.
- Yes.

1513
01:11:55,278 --> 01:11:57,914
- Don't get sick.
- Okay.

1514
01:11:57,914 --> 01:11:59,615
- You too.
- As long as we're living...

1515
01:11:59,615 --> 01:12:03,686
- Let's live a healthy, happy life.
- Yes.

1516
01:12:04,086 --> 01:12:07,590
[One Photo Can't Capture Our Life Together]

1517
01:12:09,826 --> 01:12:13,663
[As Long As Our Memories Remain Vivid,
That's All We Need]

1518
01:12:14,730 --> 01:12:18,334
[Getting Old Together]

1519
01:12:18,901 --> 01:12:22,405
[Might Be Life's Greatest Blessing]

1520
01:12:23,072 --> 01:12:26,742
<i>♪ Tears accompany our farewell. ♪</i>

1521
01:12:26,742 --> 01:12:29,745
<i>♪ A woman's life. ♪</i>

1522
01:13:06,282 --> 01:13:09,252
[Good Thing I Didn't Sing]
I wouldn't have sounded that good.

1523
01:13:09,252 --> 01:13:11,921
Why are you such a good singer?

1524
01:13:11,921 --> 01:13:14,323
Where did you learn to sing like that?

1525
01:13:17,393 --> 01:13:19,240
Oh, man.

1526
01:13:31,440 --> 01:13:32,942
My goodness.

1527
01:13:40,983 --> 01:13:43,886
[In This Place,]

1528
01:13:43,886 --> 01:13:47,390
[In This Season,]

1529
01:13:47,390 --> 01:13:51,627
[This Might Be The Last Time]

1530
01:13:51,627 --> 01:13:54,563
[We See Them Like This]

1531
01:13:56,098 --> 01:13:59,001
[We Treasure The Sound Of Their Chatter]

1532
01:13:59,001 --> 01:14:00,469
Oh, man.

1533
01:14:00,469 --> 01:14:04,907
[With Our Eyes, Ears, And Heart]

1534
01:14:05,374 --> 01:14:10,112
[Bonjour Bakery]

1535
01:14:10,613 --> 01:14:13,382
Look at you two, all cozy together

1536
01:14:13,382 --> 01:14:15,818
in the best seat in the bakery.

1537
01:14:15,818 --> 01:14:18,087
You've also received the most gifts.

1538
01:14:18,087 --> 01:14:19,555
Congratulations, ma'am.

1539
01:14:19,555 --> 01:14:20,823
Thank you.

1540
01:14:20,823 --> 01:14:23,059
It's such a pleasure to meet you.

1541
01:14:23,926 --> 01:14:25,995
Did you go to the salon today?

1542
01:14:25,995 --> 01:14:27,663
Did you get a perm?

1543
01:14:27,663 --> 01:14:29,465
- It looks great.
- Thank you.

1544
01:14:32,969 --> 01:14:35,204
What's with you?

1545
01:14:35,204 --> 01:14:36,672
I hurt my foot.

1546
01:14:36,672 --> 01:14:39,241
- Can you pass me a bag?
- Sure.

1547
01:14:39,241 --> 01:14:40,509
Why are the kitchen staff so...

1548
01:14:40,509 --> 01:14:42,611
You weren't tough guys. You were softies.

1549
01:14:42,611 --> 01:14:43,646
Seon Ho.

1550
01:14:43,646 --> 01:14:44,814
[A Lame Excuse]
I hurt my foot while walking.

1551
01:14:44,814 --> 01:14:46,549
Get out.

1552
01:14:49,585 --> 01:14:51,954
Come over here.

1553
01:14:53,089 --> 01:14:54,924
- Over here.
- That's perfect.

1554
01:14:57,259 --> 01:14:58,627
All right.

1555
01:14:58,627 --> 01:15:00,629
One, two, three!

1556
01:15:00,629 --> 01:15:02,732
- Cheese!
- Cheese!

1557
01:15:20,216 --> 01:15:21,550
- Thank you!
- Thank you!

1558
01:15:21,550 --> 01:15:23,019
- Thank you!
- Thank you!

1559
01:15:23,019 --> 01:15:24,353
Thank you!

1560
01:15:42,438 --> 01:15:44,073
This kitchen's amazing!

1561
01:15:44,073 --> 01:15:45,474
- It's huge.
- It's so impressive.

1562
01:15:45,474 --> 01:15:46,976
In the eight o'clock position.

1563
01:15:46,976 --> 01:15:48,944
That's it. It locks, right?

1564
01:15:48,944 --> 01:15:51,013
- Now turn it to the six o'clock position.
- Okay.

1565
01:15:51,013 --> 01:15:53,015
You've gotten so fast at this.

1566
01:15:53,015 --> 01:15:54,950
I'm not giving it my all.

1567
01:15:54,950 --> 01:15:56,085
But it looks really good.

1568
01:15:56,085 --> 01:15:58,621
You say that,
but I know you did your best.

1569
01:15:58,621 --> 01:16:01,023
- Over 65 years old?
- Are you sure you're over 65?

1570
01:16:01,023 --> 01:16:02,758
- Yes, I am.
- All right, then.

1571
01:16:02,758 --> 01:16:04,660
Come on in, sir.

1572
01:16:04,660 --> 01:16:06,528
- Welcome!
- Welcome!

1573
01:16:07,129 --> 01:16:09,565
You must feel nervous
with Seung Won watching.

1574
01:16:09,565 --> 01:16:11,300
My hands are shaking.

1575
01:16:11,300 --> 01:16:12,802
Take some medicine!

1576
01:16:14,003 --> 01:16:16,439
You won't earn much in the countryside.

1577
01:16:16,439 --> 01:16:18,541
What made you set up shop here?

1578
01:16:18,541 --> 01:16:20,910
- You're worried on our behalf.
- I see.

1579
01:16:21,977 --> 01:16:23,712
- That's so cute!
- This is...

1580
01:16:23,712 --> 01:16:25,347
Ma'am, you're so cute.

1581
01:16:25,347 --> 01:16:27,483
One, two, three.

1582
01:16:27,483 --> 01:16:29,118
- Move these carefully.
- Okay.

1583
01:16:29,118 --> 01:16:30,386
You need to be careful.

1584
01:16:30,386 --> 01:16:32,788
The 11 o'clock and 4 o'clock position.
That's it.

1585
01:16:32,788 --> 01:16:35,091
When the display case is full like this,
I feel proud looking at them.

1586
01:16:35,091 --> 01:16:36,826
It's fun filling the display case.

1587
01:16:36,826 --> 01:16:39,662
Take care of yourself,
and come back again sometime.

1588
01:16:39,662 --> 01:16:41,530
You're not sure you'll come back?

1589
01:16:41,530 --> 01:16:43,032
I'll definitely come back.

1590
01:16:43,032 --> 01:16:44,700
Yes, come back.

1591
01:16:44,700 --> 01:16:46,368
[Your Faces]

1592
01:16:46,368 --> 01:16:49,038
[And Your Stories]

1593
01:16:49,672 --> 01:16:51,440
[Were Just As Sweet And Awe-Inspiring]

1594
01:16:51,440 --> 01:16:55,444
[As The Vibrant Array Of Desserts]

1595
01:16:56,011 --> 01:16:59,648
[All We Did Was Offer
A Small Plate Of Our Care]

1596
01:17:00,416 --> 01:17:03,085
[And Now We Depart]

1597
01:17:03,085 --> 01:17:06,522
[With Warm And Precious Memories
That Will Stay In Our Hearts Forever]

1598
01:17:07,022 --> 01:17:08,290
We're closed.

1599
01:17:08,290 --> 01:17:09,391
Time to go home!

1600
01:17:09,391 --> 01:17:10,759
- It was a lot of fun.
- Well done.

1601
01:17:10,759 --> 01:17:11,961
Good work, everyone.

1602
01:17:11,961 --> 01:17:14,430
Why am I tearing up like this?

1603
01:17:14,430 --> 01:17:16,711
[We Hope To See You Again
When You Need A Slice Of Comfort]

1604
01:17:24,840 --> 01:17:27,076
We were so thankful these last few days.

1605
01:17:27,076 --> 01:17:29,678
- It was tasty.
- We really enjoyed the food.

1606
01:17:29,678 --> 01:17:30,946
We shared bread in the village hall.

1607
01:17:30,946 --> 01:17:32,281
- That one is good.
- Yes.

1608
01:17:32,281 --> 01:17:33,849
- The bread is delicious.
- It's all good.

1609
01:17:33,849 --> 01:17:35,017
Thank you.

1610
01:17:35,017 --> 01:17:37,620
Come again.

1611
01:17:37,620 --> 01:17:39,239
You have to come back.

1612
01:17:40,122 --> 01:17:42,691
But who knows if I'll live that long.

1613
01:17:42,691 --> 01:17:45,494
I'm 87 years old.

1614
01:17:45,494 --> 01:17:47,796
I'm nearly 90.
I don't have much time left.

1615
01:17:47,796 --> 01:17:50,733
I don't know when you'll be back,

1616
01:17:50,733 --> 01:17:53,141
but come back if you get some spare time.

1617
01:17:54,637 --> 01:17:56,277
Bye.

1618
01:17:58,040 --> 01:18:00,208
- Take good care of yourself.
- Okay.

1619
01:18:06,515 --> 01:18:07,750
[Today's Memory Diary]

1620
01:18:07,750 --> 01:18:09,418
[Title: Dad's Favorite Dessert]

1621
01:18:09,418 --> 01:18:11,487
[My Dad Was A Man Of Few Words]

1622
01:18:11,487 --> 01:18:13,889
[We Used To Enjoy A Latte And Castella]

1623
01:18:13,889 --> 01:18:16,959
[Between Trips To The Hospital
Following His Brain Hemorrhage]

1624
01:18:16,959 --> 01:18:19,195
[He Suddenly Passed Away Last Year]

1625
01:18:19,195 --> 01:18:22,097
[Whenever I See Castella,
I Think Of My Dad And It Makes Me Tear Up]

1626
01:18:22,097 --> 01:18:24,166
[Bonjour Bakery Made Me Miss Him More]

1627
01:18:24,166 --> 01:18:26,835
[I Hope You're Doing Well Up There, Dad]

1628
01:18:26,835 --> 01:18:28,504
[Title: Castella Made By Mom]

1629
01:18:28,504 --> 01:18:31,574
[Bonjour Bakery Took Me Back]

1630
01:18:31,574 --> 01:18:34,643
[To The Bread Mom Used To Make 30 Years Ago]

1631
01:18:34,643 --> 01:18:39,119
[It Was So Soft
It Just Melted In Your Mouth]

1632
01:18:39,119 --> 01:18:42,351
[I Only Learned It Was Called A Castella
After I Became An Adult]

1633
01:18:42,351 --> 01:18:44,753
[Now, I Can Never Taste That Castella Again]

1634
01:18:44,753 --> 01:18:47,289
[Every Time I Watch Bonjour Bakery,
I Miss It Even More]

1635
01:18:47,289 --> 01:18:48,958
[Title: The Unforgettable Pizza]

1636
01:18:48,958 --> 01:18:50,693
[My Grandmother Grew Up In The Countryside]

1637
01:18:50,693 --> 01:18:52,595
[So I Thought She'd Only Like Korean Food]

1638
01:18:52,595 --> 01:18:55,664
[But She Never Forgot The Pizza
She Had The First Time She Visited Me]

1639
01:18:55,664 --> 01:18:59,068
[And She Would Take Out
Her Special Stash Of Money To Get Pizza]

1640
01:18:59,068 --> 01:19:02,142
[Seeing The Seniors On Bonjour Bakery
Made Me Miss Her More]

1641
01:19:02,142 --> 01:19:06,425
[She Would Have Also Enjoyed
Those Precious And Tasty Desserts]
